, some friends encouraged me to try out for the Miss South Carolina World beauty pageant. To my surprise, I won - and was sent to New York City to compete nationally.', 70469, 0), (478440, 'What is sacred among one people may be ridiculous in another; and what is despised or rejected by one cultural group, may in a different environment become the cornerstone for a great edifice of strange grandeur and beauty.', 74910, 0), (478441, 'Every performance is different. That''s the beauty of it.', 22746, 0), (478442, 'I am obsessed with beauty. I want everything to be perfect, and of course it isn''t. And that''s a tough place to be because you''re never satisfied.', 74899, 0), (478443, 'I thought of Paris as a beauty spot on the face of the earth, and of London as a big freckle.', 12431, 0), (478444, 'I felt I had to share Idaho with my friend from New York because he''d shared New York with me, so I was going to share the beauty of nature with a man who went to museums and clubs late at night. But there was nothing to do where I lived at night.', 25077, 0), (478445, 'Beauty is the lover''s gift.', 14081, 0), (478446, 'Art is the unceasing effort to compete with the beauty of flowers - and never succeeding.', 70297, 0), (478447, 'I do not know which to prefer, The beauty of inflections, Or the beauty of innuendoes, The blackbird whistling, Or just after.', 2547, 0), (478448, 'Alas! how little does the memory of these human inhabitants enhance the beauty of the landscape!', 1049, 0), (478449, 'Whether you come from heaven or hell, what does it matter, O Beauty!', 1165, 0), (478450, 'Beauty is the oracle that speaks to us all.', 37532, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (478451, 'A whopping 89 percent of buyers start their home search online. How your house looks online is the modern equivalent of ''curb appeal.'' Rent a wide-angle lens and good lighting, get rid of your clutter and post at least eight great photos to win the beauty contest.', 34972, 0), (478452, 'There is beauty when something works and it works intuitively.', 67824, 0), (478453, 'Beauty doesn''t matter because in the end, we all lose our looks and all we have is our heart.', 61759, 0), (478454, 'Pay attention to the beauty surrounding you.', 457, 0), (478455, 'Blues and soul and jazz music has so much pain, so much beauty of raw emotion and passion.', 11155, 0), (478456, 'I didn''t grow up identifying with beauty. I grew up thinking I could be smart and funny - those are the things I got feedback on.', 2398, 0), (478457, 'Abstraction brings the world into more complex, variable relations; it can extract beauty, alternative topographies, ugliness, and intense actualities from seeming nothingness.', 19958, 0), (478458, 'I think beauty comes from within, and society paints a ridiculous picture.', 66753, 0), (478459, 'Beauty can come in strange forms.', 11508, 0), (478460, 'We have to get back to the beauty of just being alive in this present moment.', 73324, 0), (478461, 'Life is one long decay, no? There''s a lot of beauty in it. Like the patina in an old city.', 74911, 0), (478462, 'My dream is that people will find a way back home, into their bodies, to connect with the earth, to connect with each other, to connect with the poor, to connect with the broken, to connect with the needy, to connect with people calling out all around us, to connect with the beauty, poetry, the wildness.', 667, 0), (478463, 'To me, ''beauty'' means to be natural, creative, honest - to say the truth.', 8072, 0), (478464, 'I believe love at first sight is possible. Centuries of literature and art and beauty has been dedicated to that idea, so who am I to argue, even if I''ve never experienced it?', 74912, 0), (478465, 'On one hand I am this weird androgynous tomboy where I''m strangely low maintenance and have a five-minute makeup regimen. On the other I''m obsessed with all things beauty, from skin care to makeup.', 71579, 0), (478466, 'People are fighting over how our heartsongs are different. But they don''t need to be the same. That''s the beauty. We are a mosaic of gifts. Each of us has our inner beauty no matter how we look.', 22029, 0), (478467, 'I may be the first actress to admit that beauty doesn''t hold you back. I think beauty is a gift that you have to make the most of. I''ve worked hard at trying to look my best.', 52935, 0), (478468, 'Encourage good music and art and literature in your homes. Homes that have a spirit of refinement and beauty will bless the lives of your children forever.', 1826, 0), (478469, 'As we all know, there is inner beauty and outer beauty. If we examine inner beauty, to me there is nothing more beautiful than inner peace, in a man or a woman.', 74913, 0), (478470, 'When girls feel bad about their looks, 60 percent avoid normal daily activities like raising their hand in class or even going to the doctor. That means that girls do not show up for life when they don''t feel good enough or pretty enough. A role model can help girls see beauty as a source of confidence, not anxiety.', 67484, 0), (478471, 'He who seeks truth shall find beauty. He who seeks beauty shall find vanity. He who seeks order shall find gratification. He who seeks gratification shall be disappointed. He who considers himself the servant of his fellow beings shall find the joy of self-expression. He who seeks self-expression shall fall into the pit of arrogance.', 72395, 0), (478472, 'Circumstances in life often take us places that we never intended to go. We visit some places of beauty, others of pain and desolation.', 12208, 0), (478473, 'I didn''t grow up around wild horses, no. But I''ve appreciated their beauty and their power ever since I can remember.', 67877, 0), (478474, 'Some days, I know beauty techniques like it''s my job, and other days I can''t do my makeup for the life of me. So I find it easiest to just put on mineral veil and a little mascara and call it a day. I use Physician''s Formula and Bare Minerals every day of my life.', 74354, 0), (478475, 'During the ''ballad'' years for me, the politics was latent; I was just falling in love with the ballads and my boyfriend. And there was the beauty of the songs.', 7820, 0), (478476, 'In your 20s you can be pretty, but you don''t accomplish real beauty until you find wisdom and depth.', 69325, 0), (478477, 'Why is it that scuba divers and surfers are some of the strongest advocates of ocean conservation? Because they''ve spent time in and around the ocean, and they''ve personally seen the beauty, the fragility, and even the degradation of our planet''s blue heart.', 67053, 0), (478478, 'All the great religions have a place for awe, for ecstatic transport at the wonder and beauty of creation.', 1716, 0), (478479, 'High heels are like a beauty lift. In a flat, you can feel beautiful, but a stiletto changes your mood, how you move - like a wild, beautiful animal. The idea was always to follow a woman''s wardrobe, her desires.', 74672, 0), (478480, 'I would like to show that I have a heart, that I am a human being and I have feelings. And to be this kind of role model, not only for beauty pageants but also for life.', 74901, 0), (478481, 'Beauty, to me, is kind, generous, and people that are humble.', 1197, 0), (478482, 'No matter how irrelevant social class now is, even the most eager egalitarian must be quietly proud that the posh English rose is still an industry standard for peerlessly sophisticated beauty.', 74914, 0), (478483, 'Combining music, theater and comedy is a new and broader form of expression. In certain combinations you can make people laugh one moment, cry the next, and then be astounded by the beauty of the music.', 74915, 0), (478484, 'If you can visualize the whole of spring and see Paradise with the eye of belief, you may understand the utter majesty of everlasting Beauty. If you respond to that Beauty with the beauty of belief and worship, you will be a most beautiful creature.', 71936, 0), (478485, 'Perfect is boring: Beauty is irregular.', 1739, 0), (478486, 'The spirit of L.A. is untamed wilderness. It''s earthquakes and wildfires and oceans and mountain lions and fog. There''s great physical beauty.', 74916, 0), (478487, 'I love the fact that we are surrounded by this spectacular natural beauty that routinely strikes us dead. Hikers walk off into the woods and are never seen again. And still we tug on our fleece and skip off into the wilderness, not a care in the world.', 18950, 0), (478488, 'If a work of art is rich and vital and complete, those who have artistic instincts will see its beauty, and those to whom ethics appeal more strongly than aesthetics will see its moral lesson. It will fill the cowardly with terror, and the unclean will see in it their own shame.', 40, 0), (478489, 'I lend my daughter beauty products, but only as a treat. If she''s going to a party, I''ll let her borrow a mascara or moisturizer.', 22748, 0), (478490, 'Poetry allies itself with beauty - a supreme union - but never uses it as its ultimate goal or sole nourishment.', 62706, 0), (478491, 'If the universal is the essential, then it is the basis of all life and art. Recognizing and uniting with the universal therefore gives us the greatest aesthetic satisfaction, the greatest emotion of beauty.', 14276, 0), (478492, 'We know the seductive alchemy of art. To transform private anguish into a narrative of truth, if not beauty; to make sense where there was none; to bring order out of chaos - these are the promises art makes.', 51525, 0), (478493, 'Phoenix is an interesting example. Drive around and see the golf courses everywhere, and you see people''s big green lawns. And you live in a desert! I''ve always remarked about the capacity of human beings to look at somewhere and move there because of its uniqueness and its beauty and then change it.', 70918, 0), (478494, 'That''s the beauty of YouTube. You can take whatever you want and create a video from your home and put it up, and you''re just sharing it with your friends.', 68315, 0), (478495, 'I''ve always felt like an artistic person. I can''t draw or paint or sculpt. I never really had technical skills, but I''ve always felt like I appreciate really beautiful things, and part of taking a good photograph is being able to recognize beauty.', 26863, 0), (478496, 'All of the development I do is with the help of business advisors who are more like my best friends than just business people. They helped me as I created Ipsy back in 2011, which is a beauty community that ships out sampling bags to subscribers.', 66719, 0), (478497, 'Ipsy''s goal has always been to create a community that inspires women around the world to express their own unique beauty.', 66719, 0), (478498, 'Nothing is really typical of my efforts... I''m simply casting about for better ways to crystallise and capture certain strong impressions (involving the elements of time, the unknown, cause and effect, fear, scenic and architectural beauty, and other seemingly ill-assorted things) which persist in clamouring for expression.', 1060, 0), (478499, 'He who marvels at the beauty of the world in summer will find equal cause for wonder and admiration in winter.', 1069, 0), (478500, 'I think each woman has her own relationship to beauty.', 69119, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (478501, 'Life doesn''t care about your vision. Stuff happens, and you''ve just got to deal with it. You roll with it; that''s the beauty of it all.', 28896, 0), (478502, 'This quarterback Weeden can drive the ball down field. He''s a thing of beauty on throwing a football. His passing motion and his arm, frankly, you won''t see a more gifted passer, power, accuracy, the entire aspect of it.', 69678, 0), (478503, 'A woman can slip on a pair of embellished cage heels one night and a pair of streamlined, lightweight sneakers the next day. The beauty of modern luxury is the absence of rules.', 74672, 0), (478504, 'Beauty is subjective and should not be limited to only what we see on the outside.', 68265, 0), (478505, 'I meet and talk to women from every corner of this planet, and I can find beauty in each and every one of them.', 68265, 0), (478506, 'My mother never wore much make-up, and she was a kind of natural beauty; she knew just how to enhance what she had.', 70668, 0), (478507, 'I think my biggest tip - and I consider it a part of my beauty routine - is getting my sleep, without a doubt. I do a true eight hours.', 69033, 0), (478508, 'I suppose one of the challenges of writing the word-side of music these days is trying to decipher and communicate how this planet is very overwhelming at this point. The difficulties we face are overwhelming. It''s very difficult to give yourself the time to breathe and appreciate the joy and beauty that might be just right around us.', 18483, 0), (478509, 'This is so cliche and cheesy but so true - seeing how happy people get if you A. give them a beauty product or B. give them a tip that works. There''s such joy in finding a good beauty product.', 66927, 0), (478510, 'We are presented with a unique situation in the black community in that we have embraced the beauty of hip hop, the real rawness of it, the real fun of it, but we also have to address the damage it has done. We have to look at what it''s done to our black girls, especially when it comes to domestic violence.', 70493, 0), (478511, 'I am more interested in revolutionary beauty than in the great beauty, to be honest. Italian cinema is now mostly a bureau for tourism. We have given up that revolution of the contemporary.', 71074, 0), (478512, 'When I was 18, I took it for granted and was eager to move on to the bigger cities like Boston and then New York. But I''ve been to enough places to have gained a greater appreciation for the beauty and rich culture of all of Rhode Island. I am grateful for all that it offered during my childhood.', 72391, 0), (478513, 'It''s good to have a reminder that we can love ourselves and be beautiful even though we don''t really fit into certain standards of what beauty may be.', 68914, 0), (478514, 'I think that with beauty, people jump to the end instead of starting from the beginning with a good lotion or prep.', 69328, 0), (478515, 'San Francisco is a mad city - inhabited for the most part by perfectly insane people whose women are of a remarkable beauty.', 843, 0), (478516, 'Every article on these islands has an almost personal character, which gives this simple life, where all art is unknown, something of the artistic beauty of medieval life.', 22842, 0), (478517, 'For all of nature''s wonder and beauty, it is also hostile and unpredictable.', 67563, 0), (478518, 'It was Chicago with its World''s Fair which vivified the national desire for civic beauty.', 67346, 0), (478519, 'The pain passes, but the beauty remains.', 19979, 0), (478520, 'Beauty is an outward gift, which is seldom despised, except by those to whom it has been refused.', 760, 0), (478521, 'Old hands soil, it seems, whatever they caress, but they too have their beauty when they are joined in prayer. Young hands were made for caresses and the sheathing of love. It is a pity to make them join too soon.', 8, 0), (478522, 'Beauty deprived of its proper foils and adjuncts ceases to be enjoyed as beauty, just as light deprived of all shadows ceases to be enjoyed as light.', 485, 0), (478523, 'Beauty is altogether in the eye of the beholder.', 10967, 0), (478524, 'When I was young my Father used to tell me that the two most worthwhile pursuits in life were the pursuit of truth and of beauty and I believe that Alfred Nobel must have felt much the same when he gave these prizes for literature and the sciences.', 60557, 0), (478525, 'You will also allow me to thank the Academy for inviting me to lecture in Stockholm, for its hospitality, and for the opportunity afforded me for admiring the charm of your people and the beauty of your country.', 69897, 0), (478526, 'Coming in solemn beauty like slow old tunes of Spain.', 15461, 0), (478527, 'The beauty of doing film is that you construct whatever you do block by block and you can build something that will stay.', 74917, 0), (478528, 'Beauty and folly are old companions.', 1077, 0), (478529, 'As we grow old, the beauty steals inward.', 760, 0), (478530, 'Beauty is all very well at first sight but who ever looks at it when it has been in the house three days? ', 266, 0), (478531, 'When I say that human beings are just gene machines, one shouldn''t put too much emphasis on the word ''just.'' There is a very great deal of complication, and indeed beauty in being a gene machine.', 1716, 0), (478532, 'I''m just glad I was able to return to some of that innocence and beauty I had as a child when I started my own family, and my children brought me back some of that spirit.', 1380, 0), (478533, 'My everyday beauty routine is always rushed and pretty simple.', 66787, 0), (478534, 'I think permitting the game to become too physical takes away a little bit of the beauty.', 1721, 0), (478535, 'Paris is one of the most beautiful places in all the world. Unfortunately, I was so homesick I couldn''t appreciate its beauty.', 1725, 0), (478536, 'Because beauty will be so readily accessible, and skin color and features will be similar, prejudices based on physical features will be nearly eradicated. Prejudice will be socioeconomically based.', 1725, 0), (478537, 'Beauty itself is but the sensible image of the Infinite.', 1035, 0), (478538, 'Teach us that wealth is not elegance, that profusion is not magnificence, that splendor is not beauty.', 1827, 0), (478539, 'The ideal beauty is a fugitive which is never found.', 17330, 0), (478540, 'I accidentally entered a youth pageant when I was 14. That''s like a beauty pageant, but without the beauty. It was terrible.', 22856, 0), (478541, 'Part of the beauty of Silicon Valley is that people generally encourage you to think crazy. It''s the hypothesis that there''s nothing sacred that can''t be changed.', 68910, 0), (478542, 'I''m from Canada, and New Zealand feels like you took all the best bits of Canada and squished them onto a tiny island like Hawaii. I was absolutely blown away by the beauty of the South Island.', 69325, 0), (478543, 'If you go through life, and you don''t find the beauty in an unexpected place, then you really have a sad existence.', 67336, 0), (478544, 'When I look at the majority of my own songs they really came from my own sense of personal confusion or need to express some pain or beauty - they were coming from a universal and personal place.', 22705, 0), (478545, 'I sincerely feel that beauty largely comes from within.', 69119, 0), (478546, 'Beauty is a fragile gift.', 782, 0), (478547, 'I think the beauty of the writing of ''Game of Thrones'' is not that the characters are fearless; it''s how they overcome their fear, you know?', 69331, 0), (478548, 'Through Kurt I saw the beauty of minimalism and the importance of music that''s stripped down.', 22301, 0), (478549, 'I didn''t appreciate the young woman that I was, or my young beauty, because I was so obsessed with the fact that I felt fat. It''s never good to add to anybody else''s suffering. It''s an important topic to really get the gravity and the importance of - dealing with dignity.', 2324, 0), (478550, 'I''d like to grow up and be beautiful. I know it doesn''t matter, but it doesn''t hurt.', 68430, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (478551, 'The beauty about being a producer is you sit there, and you explore ideas which become a passion, which slowly becomes a reality.', 69343, 0), (478552, 'The problem with beauty is that it''s like being born rich and getting poorer.', 50885, 0), (478553, 'Surely being a Professional Beauty - let alone an ageing one - is one of the most insecure and doomed careers imaginable.', 28504, 0), (478554, 'We make such terrible mistakes with visual choices about beauty.', 22159, 0), (478555, 'I am still a victim of chess. It has all the beauty of art - and much more. It cannot be commercialized. Chess is much purer than art in its social position.', 1473, 0), (478556, 'I consider myself someone who takes a lot of beauty risks, and I''ve realized what I liar I am. I change my hair a lot, from blue to blonde to bald, but I''m trying to branch out a little more with makeup.', 60183, 0), (478557, 'Part of the beauty of Judaism, and surely this is so for other faiths also, is that it gently restores control over time. Three times a day we stop what we are doing and turn to God in prayer. We recover perspective. We inhale a deep breath of eternity.', 4059, 0), (478558, 'I have learned that acting is not about beauty.', 74289, 0), (478559, 'To me, part of the beauty of a comma is that it offers a rest, like one in music: a break that gives the whole piece of music greater shape, deeper harmony. It allows us to catch our breath.', 711, 0), (478560, 'Beauty is grace and confidence. I''ve learned to accept and appreciate what nature gave me.', 67763, 0), (478561, 'Riding my motorcycle around L.A. is like my own video game. But unlike many folks at the wheel, I am occupied with getting where I''m going and keeping myself safe. Most people are applying makeup, texting, and checking out the beauty in the next car.', 5933, 0), (478562, 'The whole beauty of music is that it goes where your words won''t let you.', 67062, 0), (478563, 'Talent survives and remains while beauty is diluted.', 67800, 0), (478564, 'Sometimes the beauty is easy. Sometimes you don''t have to try at all. Sometimes you can hear the wind blow in a handshake. Sometimes there''s poetry written right on the bathroom wall.', 1251, 0), (478565, 'Editing yourself is like an irksome coin toss. You''ve got to strip yourself of super ego and operate from the id. Maybe I''ve got my Freud mixed up. It''s just hard to trade a beauty shot for the performance with truth and a brightly lit zit.', 68459, 0), (478566, 'The past itself, as historical change continues to accelerate, has become the most surreal of subjects - making it possible... to see a new beauty in what is vanishing.', 4673, 0), (478567, 'I have always loved Reese Witherspoon and Amy Adams as role models - I read all their interviews and agree with the fundamentals of how they manage the limelight and also how they look and carry themselves. A huge part of beauty is how you carry yourself and how you deal with certain situations.', 70688, 0), (478568, 'I relax by catching up with my friends and family. When I am at home in Ibiza, I find the contrast of living on a divided island relaxing - with beauty and tranquillity in the north and a sense of fun, shallowness and celebration in the south.', 16022, 0), (478569, 'I don''t really have a beauty routine. I always use coconut oil, and I always wear mascara. That''s kind of it! I''m pretty simple.', 68464, 0), (478570, 'Here is a fundamental conflict in educated society: We are not supposed to value beauty so highly, and yet who can defend against its sheer power to move, its rhetorical force?', 74863, 0), (478571, 'My mother always called me an ugly weed, so I never was aware of anything until I was older. Plain girls should have someone telling them they are beautiful. Sometimes this works miracles.', 12987, 0), (478572, 'I like ''Zorro.'' I like people you can believe that don''t have those stupid powers. That is the beauty of Zorro. He''s just a guy working for the people, to save the people.', 52935, 0), (478573, 'I had seen the ballet of ''Swan Lake'' as a child but it was as an adult, when I saw a production featuring Erik Bruhn, that I first noticed how significant a part the ever-present threat of violence played. This juxtaposition of great beauty and grace with a backdrop of pure evil stayed with me for years.', 11749, 0), (478574, 'In Japan, the people preserve their temples for their exquisite beauty, and there are a great many sincere Buddhists; but China is irreligious: a nation of atheists or agnostics, or slaves of impious superstitions. In an extended tramp among temples, I have not seen a single male worshiper or a thing to please the eye.', 68866, 0), (478575, 'I am a great lover of art, in many forms: paintings, objets, textiles. I don''t have the talent for painting, but I have a very good sense of colour, a love of visual beauty.', 18672, 0), (478576, 'Beauty, like ice, our footing does betray; Who can tread sure on the smooth, slippery way: Pleased with the surface, we glide swiftly on, And see the dangers that we cannot shun.', 8695, 0), (478577, 'Having done a Dogme film taught me the beauty of simplicity and austerity.', 68468, 0), (478578, 'I like aristocracy. I like the beauty of aristocracy. I like the hierarchical feeling.', 9834, 0), (478579, 'I was not a good-lookin'' girl. I was extremely skinny. I wasn''t pretty. I wasn''t cool.', 25462, 0), (478580, 'Beauty is not skin-deep; it can be a means of self-affirmation, a true indicator of personality and confidence.', 71813, 0), (478581, 'How goodness heightens beauty!', 61, 0), (478582, 'Without realizing it, the individual composes his life according to the laws of beauty even in times of greatest distress.', 61, 0), (478583, 'There is no personal achievement in being born beautiful.', 44815, 0), (478584, 'Like charity, I believe glamour should begin at home.', 44815, 0), (478585, 'As soon as beauty is sought not from religion and love, but for pleasure, it degrades the seeker.', 1173, 0), (478586, 'For I must tell you that we artists cannot tread the path of Beauty without Eros keeping company with us and appointing himself as our guide.', 778, 0), (478587, 'Now, I''m not saying I''m fashionable, but there are sociological interests that matter to me, things that are theoretical, political, intellectual and also concerned with vanity and beauty that we all think about but that I try to mix up and translate into fashion.', 57414, 0), (478588, 'Fashion fosters cliches of beauty, but I want to tear them apart.', 57414, 0), (478589, 'If truth is beauty, how come no one has their hair done in the library?', 1059, 0), (478590, 'I hate the term ''arm candy.'' But, look, a woman''s figure is a beautiful thing, and if she has shapely legs, then she should show them off, because men love to see that. Not just heterosexual men - gay men like to see a woman in her beauty and the shape of her.', 68967, 0), (478591, 'There are always young bands playing in their garages. A lot of punk rock is not going to be in the mainstream. It''s below the radar. The beauty of it is that you''re not supposed to always know. It''s subterranean.', 52296, 0), (478592, 'My dad had this philosophy that if you tell children they''re beautiful and wonderful then they believe it, and they will be. So I never thought I was unattractive. But I was never one of the girls at school who had lots of boyfriends.', 74134, 0), (478593, 'The beauty of the Internet is that anybody can be a broadcaster now.', 74795, 0), (478594, 'My quick beauty tip is always have a tinted gloss of some kind to give you some color even if you have no makeup on.', 66753, 0), (478595, 'The beauty of man''s being, fashioned as he is in the fairest of forms, demonstrates the existence of the Maker, while at the same time the fact that, together with his comprehensive abilities, lodged in that fairest of forms, he soon declines and dies, demonstrates the existence of the resurrection.', 71936, 0), (478596, 'There is little premium in poetry in a world that thinks of Pound and Whitman as a weight and a sampler, not an Ezra, a Walt, a thing of beauty, a joy forever.', 1552, 0), (478597, 'Not just as a black woman, but as a woman, since the beginning of time, beauty has been our responsibility.', 68494, 0), (478598, 'After ''Freaks and Geeks,'' I dealt with several producers who wanted to cover up all my beauty marks, every single mole on my body. They tried to cover them on my first two episodes of ''Dawson''s Creek,'' and it just looked ridiculous, so I had to put my foot down. But it''s not something I''m insecure about.', 69930, 0), (478599, 'So every creative act strives to attain an absolute status it longs to create a world of beauty to triumph over chaos and convert it to order. ', 9221, 0), (478600, 'Grace is in garments, in movements, in manners; beauty in the nude, and in forms. This is true of bodies; but when we speak of feelings, beauty is in their spirituality, and grace in their moderation.', 8895, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (478601, 'It''s a good thing that beauty is only skin deep, or I''d be rotten to the core.', 2181, 0), (478602, 'I cannot go to Montreal without going to Beauty''s, my favorite place for breakfast, where I have the Mish-Mash omelet with hot dogs, salami, eggs, green peppers, and onions, and the best banana bread in the world. It''s legendary!', 69708, 0), (478603, 'Beauty and fullness of tone can be achieved by having the whole orchestra play with high clarinets and a carefully selected number of piccolos.', 49246, 0), (478604, 'Some guys say beauty is only skin deep. But when you walk into a party, you don''t see somebody''s brain. The initial contact has to be the sniffing.', 4803, 0), (478605, 'Beauty at 70 years old isn''t the same as beauty at 20 years old, but it is stunning nonetheless.', 427, 0), (478606, 'There is great beauty in going through life without anxiety or fear. Half our fears are baseless, and the other half discreditable.', 6105, 0), (478607, 'All cities are mad: but the madness is gallant. All cities are beautiful: but the beauty is grim.', 8661, 0), (478608, 'Filipinos want beauty. I have to look beautiful so that the poor Filipinos will have a star to look at from their slums.', 56084, 0), (478609, 'Personalized beauty is about each woman being able to create her own makeup routine that complements her coloring and style.', 38226, 0), (478610, 'And for me, the real world involves everything: risk, danger, beauty, energy, all we meet with in the real world.', 67421, 0), (478611, 'I also became close to nature, and am now able to appreciate the beauty with which this world is endowed.', 1784, 0), (478612, 'Having inner beauty is something you develop on your own, and I like to think I have that.', 74349, 0), (478613, 'Beauty is only skin deep. If you go after someone just because she''s beautiful but don''t have anything to talk about, it''s going to get boring fast. You want to look beyond the surface and see if you can have fun or if you have anything in common with this person.', 68514, 0), (478614, 'It''s amazing what sleep does for your looks.', 66811, 0), (478615, 'Vampires have always held a very seductive kind of lore and have always been some variety of attractive, whether it''s attractiveness that''s born of just the physical attributes that they have - this kind of ethereal beauty or translucent pallor - or whether it is more to do with the way they carry themselves.', 26628, 0), (478616, 'So far as female beauty is concerned, the Circassian women have no superiors. They have preserved in their mountain home the purity of the Grecian models, and still display the perfect physical loveliness, whose type has descended to us in the Venus de Medici.', 57546, 0), (478617, 'If you''ve never had a mother or a father, you grow up seeking something you''re never going to find, ever. You seek it in love and in people and in beauty.', 5883, 0), (478618, 'I grew up in a family where we weren''t allowed to talk about beauty or to put any emphasis on physical appearance.', 72794, 0), (478619, 'Black beauty - he''s a dark horse.', 72223, 0), (478620, 'I''m a great believer in the beauty and the power of surprise.', 894, 0), (478621, 'I''m a storyteller: the crux of the matter is to reach beauty, poetry; it doesn''t matter if that is comedy or tragedy. They''re the same if you reach the beauty.', 69160, 0), (478622, 'So, we just kind of created our own thing and that''s part of the beauty of Athens: is that it''s so off the map and there''s no way you could ever be the East Village or an L.A. scene or a San Francisco scene, that it just became its own thing.', 48866, 0), (478623, 'One of my favorite beauty products is Vincent Longo Water Canvas creamy blush. I have it in every color and I''ve been using it for 5 years and that''s all I put on when I leave the house. It looks so natural I just put a little bit on my cheeks to give them some color.', 69387, 0), (478624, 'Asian people have a unique way about them and a different sense of beauty. It''s exotic to me. I like they way Asians project their feelings. There''s a hardness to the culture, but at the same time there''s a delicateness.', 73853, 0), (478625, 'Because beauty isn''t enough, there must be something more.', 70744, 0), (478626, 'I completely agree that a sound sleep is the best beauty product. Sound sleep, one of the most important but underrated thing, helps to make you more beautiful. I can never understand how people work so hard that they miss out on their sleep.', 69775, 0), (478627, 'Red lipstick has been my beauty staple for years. I show up to Pilates or yoga at 8 A.M. wearing my red lipstick.', 67148, 0), (478628, 'I have always loved young women for their sensitive spiritual nature, gentleness, and special beauty.', 70311, 0), (478629, 'As a busy working mom I''m always pressed for time, so a quick and easy beauty routine is key!', 73158, 0), (478630, 'My mother is a beauty.', 25958, 0), (478631, 'But the beauty of Einstein''s equations, for example, is just as real to anyone who''s experienced it as the beauty of music. We''ve learned in the 20th century that the equations that work have inner harmony.', 44276, 0), (478632, 'Though beauty gives you a weird sense of entitlement, it''s rather frightening and threatening to have others ascribe such importance to something you know you''re just renting for a while.', 13191, 0), (478633, 'Beauty set up distance between other people and me. It warped their behavior.', 13191, 0), (478634, 'Even if you play perfectly, a fault of your opponent''s can destroy the entire beauty of the game.', 67912, 0), (478635, 'Remember always that the composer''s pen is still mightier than the bow of the violinist in you lie all the possibilities of the creation of beauty. ', 22784, 0), (478636, 'Especially as a title-holder, you can do great things with charities, because people suddenly care about what you have to say. I wanted to make a difference, which is why I created the Queen of the Universe pageant. I want to change all of those stigmas in the beauty pageant world.', 69028, 0), (478637, 'In the 19th century, you had bourgeois art without politics - an almost frozen idea of what beauty is.', 74513, 0), (478638, 'I love fashion, beauty, glamour. It''s the mark of civilisation.', 69101, 0), (478639, 'We live in a state with a wonderful climate and plenty of natural beauty, from the shores of Cumberland Island to the Chattahoochee River to the Blue Ridge Mountains.', 70990, 0), (478640, 'It''s how you look at beauty. Is it only an outward appearance with hair and makeup and a hot body, or is it something deeper than that?', 14576, 0), (478641, 'The very women who object to the morals of a notoriously beautiful actress, grow big with pride when an admirer suggests their marked resemblance to this stage beauty in physique.', 62388, 0), (478642, 'I can hold a cup of sake on a full moon in Japan, and the reflection of the moon in that little cup can make me feel so enthusiastic about beauty. That one good, magical moment can give me enough to create other things like the teardrop earring or necklace.', 69957, 0), (478643, 'One of the most beautiful passages of Rousseau is that in the sixth book of Confessions, where he describes the awakening in him of the literary sense. Of such wisdom, the poetic passion, the desire of beauty, the love of art for its own sake, has most.', 11179, 0), (478644, 'I can''t imagine it if beauty was the only currency I used as an actress. It just doesn''t interest me.', 68581, 0), (478645, 'My work is not about ''form follows function,'' but ''form follows beauty'' or, even better, ''form follows feminine.''', 68187, 0), (478646, 'The love of beauty in its multiple forms is the noblest gift of the human cerebrum.', 18434, 0), (478647, 'My father always taught by telling stories about his experiences. His lessons were about morality and art and what insects and birds and human beings had in common. He told me what it meant to be a man and to be a Black man. He taught me about love and responsibility, about beauty, and how to make gumbo.', 176, 0), (478648, 'Beauty and the Beast became the first animated feature ever nominated for best picture.', 70337, 0), (478649, 'But I think it is a serious issue to wonder about the other platonic absolutes of say beauty and morality.', 13538, 0), (478650, 'Beauty is everlasting And dust is for a time.', 8786, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (478651, 'I don''t like people who have never fallen or stumbled. Their virtue is lifeless and it isn''t of much value. Life hasn''t revealed its beauty to them.', 925, 0), (478652, 'I''ve backpacked to countries like Italy and Turkey and observed beautiful scenery, but then I realized that beauty was always very close to me. It is here in Belitung Island, where the rivers, beaches and the terrain captivate my attention most.', 1743, 0), (478653, '''A Court of Thorns and Roses'' was actually inspired by three of my all-time-favorite fairy/folktales: ''Beauty and the Beast,'' ''East of the Sun, West of the Moon'' and ''Tam Lin.'' I got the kernel of inspiration by wondering: ''What if ''Beauty'' was a huntress?''', 343, 0), (478654, 'Beauty is less important than quality.', 74918, 0), (478655, 'What delights us in visible beauty is the invisible.', 20540, 0), (478656, 'Beauty is the disinterested one, without which the ancient world refused to understand itself, a word which both imperceptibly and yet unmistakably has bid farewell to our new world, a world of interests, leaving it to its own avarice and sadness.', 1758, 0), (478657, 'Art ought never to be considered except in its relations with its ideal beauty.', 7208, 0), (478658, 'The truth, the absolute truth, is that the chief beauty for the theatre consists in fine bodily proportions.', 64168, 0), (478659, 'For me, a page of good prose is where one hears the rain and the noise of battle. It has the power to give grief or universality that lends it a youthful beauty.', 1717, 0), (478660, 'Beauty is not everything!', 69445, 0), (478661, 'Genetics is all about showcasing human beauty along with high-quality performance.', 74919, 0), (478662, 'I may be old-fashioned. But I believe there is such a thing as a search for beauty - a delight in the nice things in the world. And I don''t think one should have to apologise for it.', 70624, 0), (478663, '''Changes in Latitudes'' began when I was looking at a photograph of a sea turtle swimming underwater. I had such a strong feeling for the beauty of this ancient creature, at home in the sea. On the spot, I wanted to swim with that turtle. I began to imagine a character who would do just that.', 43288, 0), (478664, 'I say to the young, be happy that you were born in Italy because of the beauty of the human capital, both masculine and feminine, of this country... No other country has such human capital.', 30658, 0), (478665, 'Fashion is quite inclusive and good at embracing different things and different forms of beauty. It''s a very liberal industry. You can be yourself. Just not overweight.', 74920, 0), (478666, 'If our hearts are ready for anything, we are touched by the beauty and poetry and mystery that fill our world.', 14256, 0), (478667, 'Beauty, more than bitterness, makes the heart break.', 297, 0), (478668, 'I think everybody can be beautiful. Anybody can have beauty. It''s about how you look at the world, in a way, and how you treat yourself.', 71193, 0), (478669, 'All things are perceived in the light of charity, and hence under the aspect of beauty; for beauty is simply reality seen with the eyes of love.', 9142, 0), (478670, 'He was afflicted by the thought that where Beauty was, nothing ever ran quite straight, which no doubt, was why so many people looked on it as immoral.', 5359, 0), (478671, 'For me the greatest beauty always lies in the greatest clarity.', 3244, 0), (478672, 'There''s one more thing I want to say. It''s a touchy subject. Black beauty. Black sensuality. We live in a culture where the beauty of black people isn''t always as celebrated as other types. I''d like to help change that if I can!', 74921, 0), (478673, 'The South is very beautiful but its beauty makes one sad because the lives that people live here, and have lived here, are so ugly.', 85, 0), (478674, 'My mum is my beauty icon, because she represents what I think beauty is.', 74310, 0