rd to the wise is infuriating.', 126, 0), (478819, 'I never said most of the things I said.', 1896, 0), (478820, 'Memories are like mulligatawny soup in a cheap restaurant. It is best not to stir them.', 273, 0), (478821, 'Yield to temptation. It may not pass your way again.', 17, 0), (478822, 'If you could cross a lion and a monkey, that''s what I''d be, because monkeys are funny and lions are strong.', 68400, 0), (478823, 'Cleanliness becomes more important when godliness is unlikely.', 10731, 0), (478824, 'My definition of an intellectual is someone who can listen to the William Tell Overture without thinking of the Lone Ranger.', 4180, 0), (478825, 'A pessimist is a person who has had to listen to too many optimists.', 2692, 0), (478826, 'A child of five would understand this. Send someone to fetch a child of five.', 1040, 0), (478827, 'I don''t deserve this award, but I have arthritis and I don''t deserve that either.', 13069, 0), (478828, 'If you don''t mind, it doesn''t matter.', 13069, 0), (478829, 'Don''t forget Mother''s Day. Or as they call it in Beverly Hills, Dad''s Third Wife Day.', 9115, 0), (478830, 'Boy, those French: they have a different word for everything!', 748, 0), (478831, 'My theory is that all of Scottish cuisine is based on a dare.', 68365, 0), (478832, 'Children are smarter than any of us. Know how I know that? I don''t know one child with a full time job and children.', 544, 0), (478833, 'I went window shopping today! I bought four windows.', 13017, 0), (478834, 'I wanna make a jigsaw puzzle that''s 40,000 pieces. And when you finish it, it says ''go outside.''', 2315, 0), (478835, 'I never thought I was funny, but I enjoy being funny.', 74930, 0), (478836, 'At the end of the day it''s got to be a good movie, it''s got to be a funny movie, and it''s got to make people think, ''Hey, I couldn''t have spent my time any better.''', 13172, 0), (478837, 'To all the girls out there who think being funny is not sexy, you are wrong!', 10112, 0), 