with another person.', 2185, 0), (478869, 'Filming is a funny combination of having a good time and not being able to wait until it''s over.', 72066, 0), (478870, 'All these jokes have been pre-approved as funny by me.', 27687, 0), (478871, 'It is funny that men who are supposed to be scientific cannot get themselves to realise the basic principle of physics, that action and reaction are equal and opposite, that when you persecute people you always rouse them to be strong and stronger.', 1267, 0), (478872, 'I think it''s a comedian''s job to make everything funny. Nothing is off-limits.', 20007, 0), (478873, 'I find it funny how people from Boston and New York hate each other because of pro teams. But, like, everyone on the Red Sox is a random millionaire athlete from somewhere else.', 71962, 0), (478874, 'Sex is funny and love is serious.', 71772, 0), (478875, 'I love funny people, and when I''m with funny people, or people who are amusing in their weirdness, I love it. Because that to me is funny, as opposed to someone who stops and says, ''Hey let me tell you a joke.''', 17478, 0), (478876, 'The fact is I''m choosy, but mainly about a man''s character. He has to be interesting, funny and clever. I don''t even mind if he''s not very good-looking.', 74933, 0), (478877, 'I saw a stationery store move.', 46197, 0), (478878, 'Everything I like is either illegal, immoral or fattening.', 60508, 0), (478879, 'Its funny, because for females in general - not just in music, but the corporate ladder as well - anything we do has always been harder for us. When it comes to music, the industry wants you to conform, to look like this and to sound like this and do this or that. It makes it harder. It''s harder for us to come out and be bosses and lead the pack.', 69257, 0), (478880, 'For years I used to bore my wife over lunch with stories about funny incidents.', 388, 0), (478881, 'I did not have three thousand pairs of shoes, I had one thousand and sixty.', 56084, 0), (478882, 'I''m like old wine. They don''t bring me out very often - but I''m well preserved.', 66690, 0), (478883, 'Chaos in the midst of chaos isn''t funny, but chaos in the midst of order is.', 748, 0), (478884, 'Life can be dramatic and funny all in the same day.', 883, 0), (478885, 'I''ve thought for the last decade or so, the only actual place raw truth was seeping through in newspapers was on the Comics Pages. They were able to pull off intelligent social comment, pure truths not found elsewhere in the news pages, and had the ability to make it all funny, entertaining, and pertinent.', 28346, 0), (478886, 'There''s nothing I dislike more than being in a photo shoot where they say, ''Be yourself.'' That''s not why I became an actress. That''s what I find so funny: that you become an actor, and all of a sudden, everyone wants to know about you. But I didn''t become an actor so I could show you me.', 68181, 0), (478887, 'I''m fascinated with the stories that we tell. Real histories become fantasies and fairy tales, morality tales and fables. There''s something interesting and funny and perverse about the way fairytale sometimes passes for history, for truth.', 68560, 0), (478888, 'He looks as though he''s been weaned on a pickle.', 2203, 0), (478889, 'Every dogma has its day.', 1132, 0), (478890, 'Men are only as loyal as their options.', 2460, 0), (478891, 'I have a wonderful make-up crew. They''re the same people restoring the Statue of Liberty.', 13132, 0), (478892, 'Thinking is one thing no one has ever been able to tax.', 66718, 0), (478893, 'Every cloud has its silver lining but it is sometimes a little difficult to get it to the mint.', 2692, 0), (478894, 'I''ve never been married, but I tell people I''m divorced so they won''t think something is wrong with me.', 28346, 0), (478895, 'Moderation is a virtue only in those who are thought to have an alternative.', 2393, 0), (478896, 'All my life, I always wanted to be somebody. Now I see that I should have been more specific.', 17034, 0), (478897, 'What I am looking for is a blessing not in disguise.', 2174, 0), (478898, 'Never floss with a stranger.', 17330, 0), (478899, 'I distrust camels, and anyone else who can go a week without a drink.', 63346, 0), (478900, 'Originality is the fine art of remembering what you hear but forgetting where you heard it.', 2120, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (478901, 'Miami Beach is where neon goes to die.', 2212, 0), (478902, 'When you''re eight years old nothing is your business.', 2212, 0), (478903, 'We need two kinds of acquaintances, one to complain to, while to the others we boast.', 1014, 0), (478904, 'Turn up the lights. I don''t want to go home in the dark.', 15417, 0), (478905, 'Never fight an inanimate object.', 10731, 0), (478906, 'The only time I ever enjoyed ironing was the day I accidentally got gin in the steam iron.', 2181, 0), (478907, 'I was a vegetarian until I started leaning toward the sunlight.', 2210, 0), (478908, 'Why don''t you get out of that wet coat and into a dry martini?', 2188, 0), (478909, 'I bought some batteries, but they weren''t included.', 922, 0), (478910, 'You can do anything with bayonets except sit on them.', 552, 0), (478911, 'There is nothing in the world that I loathe more than group activity, that communal bath where the hairy and slippery mix in a multiplication of mediocrity.', 76, 0), (478912, 'I like children - fried.', 2165, 0), (478913, 'Even Napoleon had his Watergate.', 1896, 0), (478914, 'Macho does not prove mucho.', 2302, 0), (478915, 'There''s no such thing as soy milk. It''s soy juice.', 1870, 0), (478916, 'My father would take me to the playground, and put me on mood swings.', 46197, 0), (478917, 'God did not intend religion to be an exercise club.', 16940, 0), (478918, 'That''s my only goal. Surround myself with funny people, and make sure everyone has a good time and works hard.', 43216, 0), (478919, 'The next time you have a thought... let it go.', 1252, 0), (478920, 'If you can''t tell a spoon from a ladle, then you''re fat!', 2315, 0), (478921, 'It''s not so much what you learn about Mumbai, it''s what you learn about yourself, really. It''s a funny old hippie thing, but it''s true as well. You find out a lot about yourself and your tolerance, and about your inclusiveness.', 67451, 0), (478922, 'Hurried and worried until we''re buried, and there''s no curtain call, Lifes a very funny proposition after all.', 60511, 0), (478923, 'Only bad golfers are lucky. They''re the ones bouncing balls off trees, curbs, turtles and cars. Good golfers have bad luck. When you hit the ball straight, a funny bounce is bound to be unlucky.', 62911, 0), (478924, 'People want me to be funny all the time. They think I''m being funny no matter what I say or do and that''s not the case.', 69344, 0), (478925, 'I was the class podiatrist. I never made it to class clown. I wasn''t funny enough. I would examine feet and prescribe and ointment. It was a sad childhood.', 74493, 0), (478926, 'I''m really not that funny in real life! But I am the best audience one could find. I love to laugh.', 51091, 0), (478927, 'What I like best is a book that''s at least funny once in a while. What really knocks me out is a book that, when you''re all done reading it, you wish the author that wrote it was a terrific friend of yours and you could call him up on the phone whenever you felt like it. That doesn''t happen much, though.', 268, 0), (478928, 'I have only been funny about seventy four per cent of the time. Yes I think that is right. Seventy-four per cent of the time.', 67411, 0), (478929, 'During the Great Depression, when people laughed their worries disappeared. Audiences loved these funny men. I decided to become one.', 71853, 0), (478930, 'Some of the pictures I must say every now and then I just think are going to be funny. When it gets that much, you might as well just pull out all the stops and make it more of a burlesque.', 24366, 0), (478931, 'I like smart, funny, self-deprecating men.', 74934, 0), (478932, 'It''s a funny thing, the less people have to live for, the less nerve they have to risk losing nothing.', 751, 0), (478933, 'I love nerds. Comic-Con junkies are the tastemakers of tomorrow. Isn''t that funny? The tables have turned.', 66780, 0), (478934, 'I''m blonde and tanned and normal-sized! I''m sweet, shy, funny, have a big heart and I''m nice - and I like to eat.', 50391, 0), (478935, 'People ask ''do you make a conscious effort not to swear?'' - if you''re doing silly stuff you''re not tempted to put swearing in. All the comics from my childhood, who were funny without swearing, were the people that influenced me. What I do is quite traditional anyway.', 72223, 0), (478936, 'My parents are both very funny but they''re also relatively soft-spoken, normal human beings while I''m just a lunatic. I don''t know where this loud, ballsy, hammy ridiculousness came from. I''m just glad I followed my goals and my parents did too. It''s not like we even had a plan when I dragged my mom to Los Angeles.', 13298, 0), (478937, 'I heard that people were really interested in the new haircut, which I think is so funny. Great haircut, I really like it. It goes great with the time period. And I was super, super, super-happy to have my bangs swept to the side rather than straight in front of me, which I dealt with for three seasons. I''m very, very much done with that.', 70771, 0), (478938, 'Thing is, I''m a funny actor, but I''m not good at being funny. I''m going to ramble for a second: I''m an actor who can make things funny in the moment, like in stakes or in circumstances or out of character.', 66845, 0), (478939, 'As soon as you are trying to be funny or dramatic, that''s when things start feeling fake and boring.', 12986, 0), (478940, 'My grandchildren are fabulous and funny.', 405, 0), (478941, 'I love Charlie, Billy Burke''s character. Writing for him is so spectacular, he''s so funny and wry and every scene he''s in he just takes. There''s a scene in ''Eclipse'' where Bella tells him she''s a virgin, and it''s the funniest, most awkward scene I''ve ever seen on film.', 68507, 0), (478942, 'Being funny, it turns out, is like being a bank. It''s a confidence trick. As long as everyone believes in you, you are fine.', 69223, 0), (478943, 'It''s funny how I use social media because I don''t use it to promote my restaurants that much. I use it for social issues and I think that''s what it''s for. I do a few things - I mess around with music a lot because that''s a passion of mine. If something strikes me and I want to share it, I do.', 71877, 0), (478944, 'When I was in high school I used to sit by myself in the cafeteria - not necessarily by choice - but I thought it was funny to talk to people that weren''t there.', 51830, 0), (478945, 'There are just so many funny kids and teenagers. They''re just not aware of how funny they are.', 68568, 0), (478946, 'I''ve never been to a dinner party where everyone at the dinner table didn''t say something funny.', 339, 0), (478947, 'I don''t think I am particularly funny. In fact, I know I''m not.', 12899, 0), (478948, 'The funny thing is that my husband couldn''t be sweeter. He looks like this bad boy. He''s got tattoos and earrings and a mohawk, but when you talk to him and he''s around you, he''s such a gentleman. He holds doors for ladies. He pulls out chairs. He cooks. He cleans.', 72671, 0), (478949, 'The funny guy doesn''t get the girl until later in life. High school, college, everyone still wants the brooding, dangerous guy you shouldn''t have.', 67411, 0), (478950, 'My kind of wanting to be funny didn''t come from need, necessarily. The closest I can analyze it is that it was an easy way to make friends, I found out. It was just a great kind of social tool.', 67411, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (478951, 'To handle that stardom, the red carpets, the photo shoots, people all of a sudden recognizing you and following you in everyday life, it''s a bit weird. It''s strange, and it can have funny effects on you in terms of do you like it or don''t you like it. Some people run away from it, some people embrace it; I found a good middle ground.', 67701, 0), (478952, 'It''s funny how the ruthless, murderous gangster has really been romanticized by the media. I mean, I grew up watching the ''Godfathers'' and ''Scarface,'' and they were the coolest. They''re just really interesting stories with great characters. They''re rock stars.', 74935, 0), (478953, 'I don''t feel that I''m explaining the world or teaching people anything. And I''m not trying to be a mirror, showing them what''s really going on the world. All I''m trying to do is think of stuff that''s funny, just like when I''m kidding around with my friends.', 922, 0), (478954, 'When I was a kid, I never did funny things to get attention. I was never a funny person. I was never, like, ''Oh, wow. I could say this some day on stage.''', 922, 0), (478955, 'Latinos, Asians, African-Americans, women - we''re all trying to find our place in this world of cinema and television and theater. And the great thing with comedy is that most of the time, you could be orange. It doesn''t matter, as long you''re funny.', 68422, 0), (478956, 'The funny thing is that I feel close to all my characters. Deep, deep inside them all.', 496, 0), (478957, 'I''ve had an experience through music that has touched almost every part of me. It educated me in ways that I didn''t get educated in school. So we try to lay on a bit of that, through being funny, being serious, playing hard.', 2251, 0), (478958, 'I tweet from bed. I love it because it''s so quick. And it''s funny. But it also leaves a lot of room for error because new people don''t sense the sarcasm - there''s no sarcasm font.', 68024, 0), (478959, 'As a kid, I thought of myself as a funny person who secretly wanted to be serious, but now I think maybe I''m a serious person who secretly wants to be funny.', 72606, 0), (478960, 'Being funny, in some ways, is about being connected to psychology.', 72606, 0), (478961, 'When I play discos in Belfast or freshers'' week in Oxford, there are 1,800 kids dressed as me. It''s odd, it''s funny, and it pays really well.', 67705, 0), (478962, 'I do keep getting these bad girl roles. The funny thing is that, honestly, I don''t think I''m believable as these aristocratic mean girls. But I do love playing them.', 74936, 0), (478963, 'If you''re OK with being clumsy, it''s funny. But if you are super embarrassed, people are going to laugh at you.', 71806, 0), (478964, 'Unless someone wants to look funny, I''ll not recommend anyone to copy my bowling action. But on a serious note, with the confidence that I have got from the amount of runs I have been scoring, when I''m thrown the ball to bowl, I am pretty sure of what I have to do. I may not be the most attractive to watch while bowling, but I can be effective.', 66892, 0), (478965, 'I wasn''t the class clown. I wasn''t that obvious. There would be a circle of guys, and they''re watching the class clown. And I''m standing in the back, and I turn to the guy next to me and I say something funny to him, and he starts to laugh. And the guy next to him says, ''What did he say?''', 51805, 0), (478966, 'Funny thing is that the poorer people are, the more generous they seem to be.', 1300, 0), (478967, 'You just suddenly think that there''s something quite childish about acting. Basically, it''s pretending, isn''t it? It''s good fun and I enjoy it, but it''s a funny way of making a living, particularly when you make a very good wage, as I''ve been fortunate enough to do.', 73716, 0), (478968, 'I am interested in shows that are not out-and-out gag fests: you see the truth of a broken heart behind them. That is what life is like: it''s really funny, you see funny things as soon as you step out of the room, but underneath that is a whole bag of broken hearts. It''s that real pain and that real hilarity that makes life so intriguing.', 69145, 0), (478969, 'The inspiration for my Vines comes from thinking about funny and relatable experiences from my daily life.', 69245, 0), (478970, 'Objectifying is kind of a funny thing. Art is objectification, all art, because you''re taking someone and making them into an object. But people can also talk back more to you when you''re sketching them. They can look at you and say, ''Oh man, you got me wrong.''', 19819, 0), (478971, 'There''s a difference between being a comic and a comedian. A comic is a guy who says funny things, and a comedian is a guy who says things funny, and he has a style and point of view that will last much longer.', 3598, 0), (478972, 'You know what''s funny is, when I made ''Saw,'' I got accused of being a fascist; when I made ''Insidious,'' I got accused of being godless, and now I made the ''Conjuring'' films, and I''m accused of being too much God.', 69246, 0), (478973, 'It is funny to me that because I can run, because I''m athletic, people tend to see that as my only asset.', 66725, 0), (478974, 'All I know how to do is take what''s on my mind and spit it out funny. I don''t know what else I could do besides comedy.', 1252, 0), (478975, 'It''s funny - almost every comedian that I started out with moved to L.A., except for my two friends Hannibal Buress and Amy Schumer. And my two friends that are doing the best in comedy, the most successful friends I have, are Hannibal Buress and Amy Schumer.', 74551, 0), (478976, 'I''ve always liked older women. One sad thing about being my age is that there are no older women. I used to amuse my mother''s friends even at five or six with witty turns of phrase. Somehow, I just knew how to be funny.', 4223, 0), (478977, 'It''s funny how all of this has worked out - I wasn''t popular in high school, but now every drunken guy in the United States wants to be my pal. They all want to buy me a shot, and pretty soon I''m throwing up.', 56982, 0), (478978, 'Funny is funny is funny.', 51805, 0), (478979, 'Here''s the thing - I''m single, I haven''t been married, I don''t have kids yet. If I do have kids I would be interested to see them in my life, so here''s a movie for kids and I''m in there and I''m supposed to be kind of funny for kids.', 68460, 0), (478980, 'A man''s got to take a lot of punishment to write a really funny book.', 110, 0), (478981, 'With improv, it''s a combination of listening and not trying to be funny.', 70216, 0), (478982, 'The middle class is so funny, it''s the class I know best, and it''s the class where you find the most pretension, so that''s what makes the middle classes so funny.', 28, 0), (478983, 'I always just wanted to be funny. I never really planned to be scary.', 20136, 0), (478984, 'I''ve worked a lot with Noah Baumbach, and he doesn''t make it easy to like his characters, but the stories are funny and witty and there''s an edge to that kind of humanity.', 71054, 0), (478985, 'Viral videos aren''t just about being funny. They''re about identity creation.', 74937, 0), (478986, 'Some people say funny things, but I say things funny.', 53024, 0), (478987, 'It would be pretty funny to see a Beverly Hills white girl with mad rap skills.', 900, 0), (478988, 'I''m spending a year dead for tax reasons.', 386, 0), (478989, 'You can always tell when a man''s well informed. His views are pretty much like your own.', 63634, 0), (478990, 'When you''re out of sight for as long as I was, there''s a funny feeling of betrayal that comes over people when they see you again.', 71199, 0), (478991, 'I think it''s harder to go from comedy to drama than from drama to comedy. Seeing you dramatic all the time, they crave to see you being silly or funny. But, seeing you in comedy all the time, it''s hard to see that person go be serious, for some reason.', 69045, 0), (478992, 'I don''t know. I think it''s funny! I think it''s funny! I go, what? It''s so absurd. I''m alone.', 68298, 0), (478993, 'I don''t know why I get away with some things. But I''m not a misogynistic, racist person. Yet I do find those jokes funny, so I say them. And I try to say everything kind of in a good spirit.', 51885, 0), (478994, 'I''m an optimist, but an optimist who carries a raincoat.', 18461, 0), (478995, 'If I studied all my life, I couldn''t think up half the number of funny things passed in one session of congress.', 1122, 0), (478996, 'I guess when I think about it, one of the things I like to dramatise, and what is sometimes funny, is someone coming unglued. I don''t consider myself someone who is making the argument that I support these choices. I just think it can be funny.', 74494, 0), (478997, 'I''m on so late I''m definitely the last seconds of anyone''s attention. So I just want to give them something dumb to laugh at, so they go, ''That''s funny,'' then fall asleep.', 61859, 0), (478998, 'Inappropriateness is funny to me. Rudeness is hilarious.', 51830, 0), (478999, 'You''re unlikely to discover something new without a lot of practice on old stuff, but further, you should get a heck of a lot of fun out of working out funny relations and interesting things.', 66888, 0), (479000, 'I''d luv to kiss ya, but I just washed my hair.', 13058, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479001, 'Never take a solemn oath. People think you mean it.', 27345, 0), (479002, 'The four building blocks of the universe are fire, water, gravel and vinyl.', 2223, 0), (479003, 'I guess when you turn off the main road, you have to be prepared to see some funny houses.', 578, 0), (479004, 'A two-year-old is kind of like having a blender, but you don''t have a top for it.', 2195, 0), (479005, 'I see fighters make funny videos about me and stick them on Facebook and get 20 likes. When I make a video, I sell it to Fox and make seven figures. That''s the difference.', 56476, 0), (479006, 'Everything that used to be a sin is now a disease.', 2460, 0), (479007, 'I don''t follow anything blindly. I have to know the entire thing, if I have to get in to it. It might sound funny to you, but it''s like using English language. I use an English word only when I know its meaning and understand its connotation. You won''t hear me say, ''What''s up, dude'' or anything like that just for the heck of it.', 69029, 0), (479008, 'All the candy corn that was ever made was made in 1911.', 1870, 0), (479009, 'I don''t think I would do a straight late-night talk show, like a ''Tonight Show'' kind of thing. But I''m open to whatever is done well. I don''t have any agenda. I''m not like Fugazi - I''m not trying to be just so punk rock until I die. Whatever is funny is good.', 74551, 0), (479010, 'The tax collector must love poor people, he''s creating so many of them.', 5968, 0), (479011, 'Being a funny person does an awful lot of things to you. You feel that you mustn''t get serious with people. They don''t expect it from you, and they don''t want to see it. You''re not entitled to be serious, you''re a clown.', 18086, 0), (479012, 'There''s a darkness under ''The Hangover'' because ultimately there''s a missing person and it''s not really that funny. There''s a sort of darkness under it that I love, and still people are laughing as hard if not harder than they did in ''Old School.''', 66930, 0), (479013, 'Memories are doing funny things to us.', 68605, 0), (479014, 'I''ve always wanted to go to Switzerland to see what the army does with those wee red knives.', 4180, 0), (479015, 'I love to go to Washington - if only to be near my money.', 13132, 0), (479016, 'I spent a year in that town, one Sunday.', 1643, 0), (479017, 'I want my children to have all the things I couldn''t afford. Then I want to move in with them.', 2181, 0), (479018, 'I think Irish women are strong as horses, incredibly loyal and for the most part, funny, witty, bright and optimistic in the face of devastating reality.', 74938, 0), (479019, 'I consider that a man''s brain originally is like a little empty attic, and you have to stock it with such furniture as you choose.', 764, 0), (479020, 'If it''s the Psychic Network why do they need a phone number?', 2185, 0), (479021, 'I''d rather not have a moment when I''m known for my looks being funny and interesting lasts longer.', 74939, 0), (479022, 'It''s obviously funny to be a meme, so I could be down with it in that regard, but it also belittles one''s art.', 72592, 0), (479023, 'Films are big hits when they touch a lot of people. Things are not funny in a vacuum, they''re funny because we respond to some personal dislocation, some embarrassment, some humiliation, some pain we''ve suffered, or some desire we have.', 28896, 0), (479024, 'When I turned about 12 or 13, I realised that being funny wasn''t about remembering jokes. It was about creating them.', 71063, 0), (479025, 'Maybe people don''t see me as believable playing a person of today. I guess I''m just more realistic in a corset and funny hairstyles.', 74936, 0), (479026, 'Progress might have been alright once, but it has gone on too long.', 2247, 0), (479027, 'I am a marvelous housekeeper. Every time I leave a man I keep his house.', 2302, 0), (479028, 'You know, you can touch a stick of dynamite, but if you touch a venomous snake it''ll turn around and bite you and kill you so fast it''s not even funny.', 15778, 0), (479029, 'Conversation would be vastly improved by the constant use of four simple words: I do not know.', 10019, 0), (479030, 'In comic strips, the person on the left always speaks first.', 1003, 0), (479031, 'Do not let a flattering woman coax and wheedle you and deceive you she is after your barn.', 3287, 0), (479032, 'A lot of baby boomers are baby bongers.', 69746, 0), (479033, 'Being a stand-up is my mission in life; it''s my passion. My ongoing goal is to simply be funny, on my own, in front of a roomful of strangers.', 2195, 0), (479034, 'My mum passing away wasn''t funny, but that funeral and what I went through, the things that happened, looking back at it, there were funny moments. You have to be strong enough to look back at it, to sit and assess the situation.', 44935, 0), (479035, 'Being a humorist is not a voluntary thing. You can tell this because in a situation where saying a funny thing will cause a lot of trouble, a humorist will still say the funny thing. No matter how inappropriate.', 10731, 0), (479036, 'The men I idolized built their bodies and became somebody - like Sylvester Stallone and Arnold Schwarzenegger - and I thought, ''That can be me.'' So I started working out. The funny thing is I didn''t realize back then that I was having a defining moment.', 11331, 0), (479037, 'Whatever is funny is subversive, every joke is ultimately a custard pie... a dirty joke is a sort of mental rebellion.', 521, 0), (479038, 'I like drama. I love being in a drama where I get to be the funny guy. That''s what I really love the most.', 17495, 0), (479039, 'It''s funny the way most people love the dead. Once you are dead, you are made for life.', 92, 0), (479040, 'There''s also a certain rhythm to the way Jews talk that might be funny.', 51334, 0), (479041, 'I get asked, ''Who would you really like to work with?'' I''m already working with them. Smart, 