INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479051, 'I love readings and my readers, but the din of voices of the audience gives me stage fright, and the din of voices inside whisper that I am a fraud, and that the jig is up. Surely someone will rise up from the audience and say out loud that not only am I not funny and helpful, but I''m annoying, and a phony.', 457, 0), (479052, 'I never liked apples. In fact, when I was a little girl, my mom wanted to give me apples in my lunch box and I would ask for green peppers. So bizarre... It''s funny - I don''t have an apple a day, but I can say that I have a few a week.', 1624, 0), (479053, 'The funny thing is, I''ve never really hurt myself in an action movie. I''ve done ''Wanted,'' ''X-Men,'' ''Welcome To The Punch,'' even ''Trance'' to a certain extent has little bits of action and stuff, but I''ve never really hurt myself at all - not even like a sprained ankle.', 70221, 0), (479054, 'Isn''t it funny how babies laugh a lot? I read a toddler, a young child laughs 300 times a day. The average adult laughs, like, four times a day. God put it in them. He put the laugh in us, but I think sometimes we let life get us down, you know, have bad breaks, and we lose our breaks.', 3956, 0), (479055, 'Almost anything can be funny if said the right way - but it has to be said the right way.', 44935, 0), (479056, 'I do not think that obsession is funny or that not being able to stop one''s intensity is funny.', 66893, 0), (479057, 'Well in the book Carrie was my alter ego. In real life, Sarah Jessica and I don''t look anything alike. But people do say that we sound alike. Sarah Jessica is an adorable girl and she is very funny.', 66, 0), (479058, 'It''s funny because it''s funny.', 74940, 0), (479059, 'I could party in a cardboard box with people who are funny and don''t care. For me, it''s really about who I surround myself with, so I just try to always be with hilarious people.', 68388, 0), (479060, 'I think there have always been funny women, from Carol Burnett to Joan Rivers. When the audience sees a woman, they innately know she''s worked twice as hard to get there, she''s had to prove that she can be the leader, first, and then be funny on top of it. She has to emit a confidence that she''s in control.', 27946, 0), (479061, 'My father was a really funny guy. He lived a good long life. And he was the reason I wanted to be funny and become a comedian and a comedy writer, so to say that he''s somewhat of a mythic figure in my life would be an understatement.', 74149, 0), (479062, 'I don''t mean to be funny.', 1896, 0), (479063, 'I remember straightening my hair because I wanted to be like everybody else, and now the fact that anybody would emulate what I do? It''s just funny.', 100, 0), (479064, 'It''s funny, in literature no one ever goes to the lavatory.', 26772, 0), (479065, 'I can be dramatic. I can be funny. I can be sexy. I can be sad. I can be glad.', 72996, 0), (479066, 'It''s funny, because there are so many stereotypes out there about actors and movie stars in general, but I''ve had a great opportunity to meet a lot of them, and maybe it''s just because they don''t behave that way around me, but I rarely see that kind of abuse of power.', 69249, 0), (479067, 'I''m very lighthearted, outgoing, friendly, and funny, so I like to try new things.', 74377, 0), (479068, 'I try to be funny and not ignorant.', 44935, 0), (479069, 'There''s a fine line between angry and grumpy. Angry isn''t nice, but grumpy is funny.', 73217, 0), (479070, 'Eyebrows are really important because they structure the face. In school it was funny because I was always the one walking around with tweezers plucking my girlfriends'' eyebrows. I was really good; eyebrow tweezing runs in my family - my mother used to do mine, and I picked it up.', 68240, 0), (479071, 'Most of my show is true; like, 90% of everything I say on stage is true. I just have to find the way to make it funny - that''s the difficult thing.', 1515, 0), (479072, 'The thing I most hate about the Left is that they want to stop us laughing - to prescribe which jokes are OK and which are not OK to make in public and to draw artificial lines around certain subjects. I find all sorts of inappropriate things funny.', 8420, 0), (479073, 'A reputation takes years and years and years to build, and it takes one press of a button to ruin it. Don''t let that happen to you. You''ve done so much work; you''ve put in so much effort. Don''t let one moment ruin your entire life because you wanted to be funny or you were mad or because you had a mood.', 69347, 0), (479074, 'I''m a prankster, so some of the - you know, I like a good joke. I think when it''s funny, it''s funny.', 73776, 0), (479075, 'Certainly there are things in life that money can''t buy, but it''s very funny - Did you ever try buying them without money?', 2247, 0), (479076, 'I was the kid next door''s imaginary friend.', 47639, 0), (479077, 'With my boyfriend, we can make sexist jokes to each other because we know it''s absolutely not true. If I get home from a long day and he says: ''Go on, get in the kitchen,'' it''s funny because we know it''s not our lives.', 74546, 0), (479078, 'It''s grueling never knowing if the audience is going to think you''re funny. It''s soul-destroying when they don''t laugh.', 68497, 0), (479079, 'It''s funny how God will just keep using you, and our motto around our family forever has been, ''Just let Him use you.''', 71656, 0), (479080, 'It''s funny how seeing a love story never gets boring, because it''s the dream, isn''t it? It''s the dream to have a true connection with another human being.', 69501, 0), (479081, 'As far as I''m concerned, ''whom'' is a word that was invented to make everyone sound like a butler.', 2232, 0), (479082, 'I think they should have a Barbie with a buzz cut.', 1217, 0), (479083, 'California is a fine place to live - if you happen to be an orange.', 13077, 0), (479084, 'He was like a cock who thought the sun had risen to hear him crow.', 215, 0), (479085, 'An optimist is a fellow who believes a housefly is looking for a way to get out.', 6546, 0), (479086, 'Say what you will about the ten commandments, you must always come back to the pleasant fact that there are only ten of them.', 411, 0), (479087, 'It is even harder for the average ape to believe that he has descended from man.', 411, 0), (479088, 'The reason there are two senators for each state is so that one can be the designated driver.', 9115, 0), (479089, 'Every man''s dream is to be able to sink into the arms of a woman without also falling into her hands.', 2216, 0), (479090, 'You see much more of your children once they leave home.', 1814, 0), (479091, 'My uncle Sammy was an angry man. He had printed on his tombstone: What are you looking at?', 21932, 0), (479092, 'If men knew how women pass the time when they are alone, they''d never marry.', 15417, 0), (479093, 'Because of their size, parents may be difficult to discipline properly.', 10731, 0), (479094, 'Every man has a sane spot somewhere.', 449, 0), (479095, 'I never liked you, and I always will.', 31112, 0), (479096, 'Include me out.', 31112, 0), (479097, 'One of the disadvantages of wine is that it makes a man mistake words for thoughts.', 2087, 0), (479098, 'Fashions have done more harm than revolutions.', 98, 0), (479099, 'The reward of energy, enterprise and thrift is taxes.', 5249, 0), (479100, 'I don''t believe in the after life, although I am bringing a change of underwear.', 281, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479101, 'The day I made that statement, about the inventing the internet, I was tired because I''d been up all night inventing the Camcorder.', 13473, 0), (479102, 'So, where''s the Cannes Film Festival being held this year?', 11155, 0), (479103, 'Me carrying a briefcase is like a hotdog wearing earrings.', 65137, 0), (479104, 'My mother was against me being an actress - until I introduced her to Frank Sinatra.', 74941, 0), (479105, 'Food, love, career, and mothers, the four major guilt groups.', 11928, 0), (479106, 'Defy your own group. Rebel against yourself.', 11928, 0), (479107, 'I was born in very sorry circumstances. Both of my parents were very sorry.', 74942, 0), (479108, 'It is easy for me to love myself, but for ladies to do it is another question altogether.', 67052, 0), (479109, 'I''d never been in play long enough for the flowers to die in the dressing room.', 71443, 0), (479110, 'I was sleeping the other night, alone, thanks to the exterminator.', 47639, 0), (479111, 'God writes a lot of comedy... the trouble is, he''s stuck with so many bad actors who don''t know how to play funny.', 1205, 0), (479112, 'It''s funny how sometimes how the public some people think I was born like this. That I maybe I sleep and I do big muscle, but its a lot of work to look like this and to be in this kind of condition.', 29646, 0), (479113, 'I can do comedy, so people want me to do that, but the other side of comedy is depression. Deep, deep depression is the flip side of comedy. Casting agents don''t realize it but in order to be funny you have to have that other side.', 67023, 0), (479114, 'In my circle of friends, I''ve always been loud and funny and talkative. But as soon as I step out of that circle, I get very quiet and introspective. I don''t want the spotlight on me.', 64894, 0), (479115, 'Well, I''m not afraid to say something if I think it''s funny, even if it''s harsh or racist.', 18382, 0), (479116, 'I write funny. If I can make my wife laugh, I know I''m on the right track. But yes, I don''t like to get Maudlin. And I have a tendency towards it.', 3212, 0), (479117, 'I have no agenda except to be funny. Neither I or the writers profess to offer any worldly wisdom.', 70041, 0), (479118, 'Half of the great comedians I''ve had in my shows and that I paid a lot of money to and who made my customers shriek were not only not funny to me, but I couldn''t understand why they were funny to anybody.', 71750, 0), (479119, 'People don''t realize that I''m really funny and I''m an excellent bridge player.', 2066, 0), (479120, 'You gotta keep the funny intact.', 12824, 0), (479121, 'One thing the blues ain''t, is funny.', 60173, 0), (479122, 'We have never been strictly political, only strictly funny.', 69204, 0), (479123, 'About 100 things that your kid will do that will surprise you and break your heart and it will be a combination of fact based therapy, medically advised kinds of passages accompanied by celebrity anecdotes and just some funny stuff to lighten the load.', 68389, 0), (479124, 'I wasn''t very funny or flashy, I was kind of boring.', 68314, 0), (479125, 'But I think Kiss Kiss, Bang Bang really got that thing where, if a movie reads really funny and then has some dramatic or violent or sinister stuff in it, you can''t forget that primarily it has to be even funnier than you read it or that other stuff doesn''t work.', 69284, 0), (479126, 'When I tell people I''m a comedian they say, ''Oh, are you funny?'' I say, ''No, it''s not that kind of comedy.''', 5975, 0), (479127, 'I used to think that everything was just being funny but now I don''t know. I mean, how can you tell?', 321, 0), (479128, 'I don''t need somebody behind a desk to tell me what a marketing survey says is funny. I got 3 million miles and 70,000 tickets sold, telling me that I know how to make people laugh.', 71984, 0), (479129, 'Eddie Drake is sort of this loose cannon, funny, edgy guy, who has this really foolish, foolish mustache.', 74834, 0), (479130, 'Steve Martin is one of the most intelligent, well-read human beings that I''ve ever come across. He is equally as funny off screen as he is on. But he also has a very intellectual side, and he''s a really nice human being. We actually become good friends.', 74943, 0), (479131, 'I had gotten to a place where I truly believed everything I was called: ''not sexy,'' ''not funny,'' ''too intense,'' desperate.'' All those labels they gave me, I took them because there wasn''t a trace of my true self left.', 67575, 0), (479132, 'I wanted to be that quirky girl who writes funny songs that still have meaning.', 746, 0), (479133, 'There are a lot of funny people and a lot of unfunny people. Some of them are women and some of them are dudes.', 70264, 0), (479134, 'We''ve seen some insane signs: ''Is that a loaf of bread in your pocket, or are you just happy to see me?'' Funny stuff along those lines. Very original. One just said, ''I will do unspeakable things.'' I thought that was very interesting - and mildly terrifying!', 69760, 0), (479135, 'I put on a big show when I write something I think is funny.', 20596, 0), (479136, 'I tend to play characters that I can infuse with certain kinds of humour. Even the baddest guy can be funny in his own particular way. I want the audience to engage with the character on some deeper level so that they leave the cinema still thinking about him.', 73054, 0), (479137, 'It''s funny - in elementary school, I went by Amber. I never liked Tiffani.', 74944, 0), (479138, 'I think I''ve got a funny face.', 74945, 0), (479139, 'I mean, I''m married first of all to one of, if not the most wonderful women in the world. She is everything - funny, attractive, hard-working, she has integrity, she loves me to bits.', 70614, 0), (479140, 'You know being relevant or coming up with something interesting, funny to say about what''s current is just as hard as it might ever be depending on the serendipity of it all.', 1059, 0), (479141, 'I turned down ''Some Like It Hot.'' See how smart I am? I felt I couldn''t bring anything funny to it. The outfit was funny. I don''t need to compete with the wardrobe.', 2216, 0), (479142, 'I don''t really need to be dirty to be funny.', 56982, 0), (479143, 'I never know when I am being funny, and the other way too. I don''t think you can think about that. I don''t think you can try to be funny. Some people are just funny.', 67388, 0), (479144, 'Funny enough, if you are looking at people these days who are putting Botox in their face and getting all sorts of plastic surgery, we look at them and go, I can tell you''ve had Botox. I can tell you''ve had plastic surgery. You look really strange to me. But no one''s saying anything. We''re just accepting the fact that they''re strange-looking.', 69518, 0), (479145, 'It is funny what a year can do.', 74446, 0), (479146, 'Sixth grade was a big time, in my childhood, of hoops and friendship, and coming up with funny things.', 68361, 0), (479147, 'There''s always something funny about men chasing women.', 74940, 0), (479148, 'I''m never afraid to try something if I think it''s funny. And I know I''ll regret it if I don''t.', 68360, 0), (479149, 'If Joy Behar or Sherri Shepherd was a dude, they''d be off TV. They''re not funny enough for dudes. What if Roseanne Barr was a dude? Think we''d know who she was?', 16775, 0), (479150, 'Being mean just for being mean''s sake isn''t funny.', 74946, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479151, 'Gotta stay in the gym, stay funny, stay sharp. I just love working.', 68400, 0), (479152, 'I think there''s something in the fact that it''s hard to be good looking and funny. You have to have an oddball quality people have to sympathise with you to find you funny. ', 74847, 0), (479153, 'That''s a funny thing, fame. People definitely do treat you differently. When you begin to be successful, people say, ''Don''t go changing.'' Well, that''s easy to say, but the fact is, you don''t change at all - other people do.', 74947, 0), (479154, 'I think that ''Hangover II'' is as funny as ''The Hangover I,'' honest to God, but I think that it''s a little bit darker, and the stakes are a little bit higher.', 66930, 0), (479155, 'It''s funny when you know you''re playing two characters and you''re aware of how you have to play each one into your performance of the other. You''re constantly at the back of your mind thinking and it all gets a bit confusing.', 70679, 0), (479156, 'I would love to write a mystery - a romantic, funny mystery.', 413, 0), (479157, 'A lot of comedies are based on the reaction shot. You have one person doing something stupid and one person is generally the straight man, and the laughs generally come on the reaction of the straight man to the funny thing the other person has done.', 14206, 0), (479158, 'I always thought ''chick lit'' meant third-person contemporary funny novels, dealing with issues of the day. I mean, it''s not the ideal term; when I''m asked to describe what I do, I say I write romantic comedies, cause that''s what I feel they are. But I''m quite pragmatic.', 173, 0), (479159, 'Being effective at social media, whether for business or personal use, means capturing people who have short attention spans. They''re only a click away from a picture of a funny cat, so you have to make your thing more compelling than that cat. And that can be a high bar.', 34933, 0), (479160, 'You know, what''s funny to one person is not at all to someone else.', 47094, 0), (479161, 'I always find it funny when I watch actors talking about, ''I chose to do this part.'' A lot of times it''s ''you''re lucky to get the job.'' We''re like, ''Thank you so much.''', 74434, 0), (479162, 'Lot of ugly funny dudes end up with some pretty gorgeous women. Women are much deeper than us in choosing a mate - they see in the long term.', 6537, 0), (479163, 'Yes, we do defend our office as we do defend our homes. This is a constitutional right everybody has, and nothing''s funny about that. The only reason they get mad at the Black Panther Party when you do it is for the simple reason that we''re political.', 50645, 0), (479164, 'Children are the most honest critics. They will say ''You''re funny'', but also ''You''re pathetic - go away.''', 1479, 0), (479165, 'I find being funny very hard work. I am always asked about it, and I feel guilty saying that, but it''s the truth. I love my work, but it ain''t easy.', 74948, 0), (479166, 'I think stutterers are funny. And I know it''s rude and politically incorrect to laugh at stutterers. But I think it is okay because I know why they''re funny. They make people nervous. People think, when on earth are they going to get the word out, so they start laughing out of their own nervousness.', 72902, 0), (479167, 'What bothers most critics of my work is the goofiness. One reviewer said I need to make up my mind if want to be funny or serious. My response is that I will make up my mind when God does, because life is a commingling of the sacred and the profane, good and evil. To try and separate them is fallacy.', 105, 0), (479168, 'If something is shocking without being funny it''s hard to justify.', 12824, 0), (479169, 'On ''The Simpsons,'' I will say that we definitely like to comment on what''s going on in the world, and we try to be funny. If we can figure out a way of being funny about it, then we''ve gone part of the way of accomplishing our task.', 538, 0), (479170, 'I think Amy Poehler and Tina Fey have done so much for women in comedy in the sense that they''ve normalized it. You don''t think, ''I''m going to watch that comedy starring a woman,'' you think, ''I''m going to watch that funny show.'' They refuse to play the foils for men, or be reduced to the butt of every joke, and I love that about both of them.', 73173, 0), (479171, 'I grew up in a time when women didn''t really do comedy. You had to be homely, overweight, an old maid, all that. You had to play a stereotype, because very attractive women were not supposed to be funny - because it''s powerful; it''s a threat.', 1059, 0), (479172, 'Someone said to me at a party once, ''Oh, yeah, you''re a comedian? Then how come you''re not funny now?'' And I just wanted to say, ''Well, I''m just going to take this conversation we''re having and then repeat that to strangers, and then that''s the joke. You''re the joke later.''', 15814, 0), (479173, 'My ideal prom date would have to be cute, funny, sweet, nice.', 68261, 0), (479174, 'I think it would be funny for people to read in obituaries of me that my major contribution to the arts was the popularization of the phrases ''neutral facial expression'' and ''screaming in agony.''', 5234, 0), (479175, 'I get a kick out of people saying I was funny.', 12902, 0), (479176, 'As a youngster, my mother and father always drilled into my head having something to fall back on. My father was kind of funny. I''d score 40 points. I''d come home and say, ''Look dad, I scored 40.'' He''d never have a smile on his face. He''d be like, ''I saw that move you did. What if you''d hurt your knee?''', 66772, 0), (479177, 'I remember people saying: ''You look funny, your hair is so black, you have a flat nose,'' but I didn''t think of it being racism, and I still don''t. But there was a sense of difference, of being an outsider.', 6937, 0), (479178, 'You shouldn''t get too close to the truth, because then maybe you stop being funny.', 51805, 0), (479179, 'I know that I''m going to die and that you''re going to die. I can''t do anything about that. But I can explore it through a metaphor and make a kind of funny, dark story about it, and in doing so, really exhaust and research as many aspects of it as I can imagine. And in a way, that does give me some closure.', 30, 0), (479180, 'I''ve always surrounded myself with funny people.', 68491, 0), (479181, 'I try to write stories that are thrilling and full of mystery and funny all at the same time, stories that raise moral questions but come up with very few moral answers, stories that emotionally touch readers through the characters.', 74949, 0), (479182, 'I think funny is just the foundation. I don''t really think, to some extent, funny is the absolute most important thing. It should also communicate some idea through the medium of cartooning. Just to be funny is... You know what, the things that you laugh hardest at aren''t cartoons.', 68622, 0), (479183, 'Every girls'' night needs a funny movie and a good conversation about guys! My friends and I also love picking outfits out for each other to try on at slumber parties. It''s so fun.', 69388, 0), (479184, 'When I was right out of college, I felt competitive with some of the guys in my class over career stuff. It''s funny now to think about it - that a friend getting a job or something had anything to do with me... I think that my relationship with my wife has played a pivotal role in the chilling out of Aaron.', 74950, 0), (479185, 'I always have a funny story at communion time that underscores that no one is perfect, and that communion is not for perfect people but for hungry people.', 74537, 0), (479186, 'I love to swim. When I jump in the water, I feel like I''m 12 years old again. It''s really funny how it does that to me.', 67751, 0), (479187, 'When Jonathan Winters died, it was like, ''Oh, man!'' I knew he was frail, but I always thought he was going to last longer. I knew him as being really funny, but at the same time, he had a dark side.', 2185, 0), (479188, 'I was a good student until I turned 15. Then, all of a sudden, it didn''t matter to me anymore. Isn''t that funny. I don''t want to go to college. I always knew that. But it''s hard. My friends are going, and I feel a little left behind.', 74951, 0), (479189, 'The gummy bears tattoo was my idea. It''s my son''s favorite candy. The sketch was my other son''s idea. It''s a self-portrait of himself. I just showed the artist his sketch and had him tattoo it on my forearm. It looks like a stick person with big hair. It''s pretty funny.', 69301, 0), (479190, 'The real world has always been far more exciting and funny and dangerous to me than anything somebody could conjure up sitting in front of a computer.', 72380, 0), (479191, 'I love playing smart and tough and having funny lines.', 70352, 0), (479192, 'There are a lot of funny things that happen in one''s life.', 67399, 0), (479193, 'I love my brothers'' kids. It''s funny - as an uncle, you become so protective of them.', 33023, 0), (479194, 'The human brain is a funny thing: it''s very susceptible to tempo and melody. You put the right words to it, and it becomes very influential.', 74952, 0), (479195, 'It''s funny how you get a bit older and become more accepting of things. When you''re in your twenties, you''re skeptical of everything. I definitely felt like that.', 70679, 0), (479196, 'My job is to bring the tickle. I know what''s funny.', 70080, 0), (479197, 'I make funny videos of me playing video games, and I share those moments.', 13042, 0), (479198, 'I''m screamingly funny, you know, I really am in the books. And that helps because I''m funnier than a lot of people, I think, and that''s appreciated by young people.', 13666, 0), (479199, 'Rapping can be repetition sometimes. Sometimes you gotta highlight your words in a certain kind of way. So I always was a fan of sing-rapping. It was always funny to me a little bit, and I think that being funny and being able to laugh, even at yourself, is a form of flattery.', 71437, 0), (479200, 'I seem to get into situations that make people laugh, but I don''t consider myself that funny of a person. I''m not witty. I''m kind of slow in conversations. I''m not that articulate with jokes. The first time I made stuff and screened it for an audience, I was surprised what people were laughing at.', 74953, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479201, 'I always believe that funny is serious and serious is funny. You don''t really need a distinction between them.', 1515, 0), (479202, 'Sometimes I''m really funny, sometimes I''m quiet, sometimes I''m shy, but I''m constantly changing.', 74737, 0), (479203, 'There are precedents for what happens when societies allow the divide between rich and poor to get so huge that it stops being funny and starts becoming a sick, blood-boiling joke. If you had a Tardis, you could go back to 1917 and ask the Russian royal family how it was all going.', 27413, 0), (479204, 'When it comes down to it, glam rock was all very amusing. At the time, it was funny, then a few years later it became sort of serious-looking and a bit foreboding.', 1232, 0), (479205, 'I did feel funny about being fair and having red hair and freckles. I did not like that because I grew up in a neighbourhood where no one had red hair. I felt very conspicuous but not in a nice way.', 73616, 0), (479206, 'It''s funny: most people who recognize me on the subway and stuff - it''s much more they think of me as a funny guy. I get much more of people telling me how much I make them laugh, actually. Which is nice.', 70611, 0), (479207, 'In person, my father is so friendly, so considerate, so funny, and so real. I have admired my father all of my life, and I love him with all my heart.', 74954, 0), (479208, 'I don''t argue with people... if they say I''m not funny, they''re right, for them.', 69726, 0), (479209, 'If you look at shows like ''Def Comedy Jam'' in its heyday, there were so many really funny, talented black comics that never would have gotten on that show because they just weren''t doing comedy that fit that mold.', 61882, 0), (479210, 'I feel like, if there''s an elephant in the room, I''d really like to start off by introducing the elephant in the room. And sometimes it''s funny.', 70667, 0), (479211, 'I''m going to take this God-given gift of being funny, and I''m going to spread it out like peanut butter on everything I do.', 385, 0), (479212, 'I auditioned for a movie recently, and when I went in, the producer said he''d told one of its stars, Naomi Watts, that he was auditioning me, and she''d said, ''She''s so funny; she''s a great actress - you should hire her.'' What a lovely, kind, and supportive thing to do for another woman.', 67089, 0), (479213, 'If you don''t have anything nice to say, don''t say it at all. And if you do have to say it, make it really funny so I can screenshot it and save it for later.', 69924, 0), (479214, 'I think politics is extremely funny in and of itself.', 74955, 0), (479215, 'It''s funny how God will change your plans for you when he''s ready.', 72874, 0), (479216, 'My friend and I founded the New York Arab-American Comedy Festival to counter the negative images of Arabs in media. And we always made sure that the comedy came first. So we weren''t a bunch of Arabs trying to be funny. We were a bunch of comedians who just happened to be of Arab heritage.', 68025, 0), (479217, 'We spend a lot of time on Skype and other video interviews, and it''s funny how many people will prepare for a Skype interview by wearing a formal suit jacket with pajama pants on the bottom. Then suddenly, someone is at the door, and you have to get up, and you realize you''re wearing reindeer boxers. Just put pants on.', 67682, 0), (479218, 'I want to give kids that fall-off-the-bed-laughing feeling. Either that, or the sixth-grade feeling that life is hard - sometimes unbearably hard - and it is ultimately about death. But in the meantime, life can be really funny, too.', 37029, 0), (479219, 'The music industry is really funny, when you have a hit record, everyone knows who are you, everyone wants to do duets with you, then if you have a miss, people suffer from amnesia.', 70614, 0), (479220, 'I had an idea of what I thought was funny. It''s kind of based on how I am.', 883, 0), (479221, 'But you can''t focus on things that matter if all you''ve been is asleep for forty years. Funny how sleep rhymes with sheep. You know.', 23240, 0), (479222, 'The word ''funny'' is a bit like the word ''love'' - we don''t have enough words to describe the many varieties.', 1047, 0), (479223, 'A lot of modern comedies are difficult to watch too, because they''re so ironic and so detached and so quote-unquote clever. They kind of keep you at arm''s length. They can be really funny, but they''re not really nourishing.', 69808, 0), (479224, 'I''d love to do a comedy. I''m terrified of comedy. I don''t think I''m funny, but I guess that''s why it''s so thrilling.', 52952, 0), (479225, 'There is nothing funny about a well-adjusted, intelligent person making the right choices.', 43876, 0), (479226, 'Like almost everyone who uses e-mail, I receive a ton of spam every day. Much of it offers to help me get out of debt or get rich quick. It would be funny if it weren''t so exciting.', 1133, 0), (479227, 'I''m undaunted in my quest to amuse myself by constantly changing my hair.', 66567, 0), (479228, 'When I''m on stage, it''s really intense. My mind is going a million miles an hour, trying to remember my act, trying to say it all the right way. It''s funny how different it looks and how it''s happening. There are three Fellini circuses in my head, and outwardly it looks like I''m going to get a bagel.', 922, 0), (479229, 'You know how old I am? I''m so old, I remember when Letterman used to be funny and it was presidents who were serious. That''s how old I am.', 17531, 0), (479230, 'The superfluous, a very necessary thing.', 808, 0), (479231, 'It''s funny how you never think about the women you''ve had. It''s always the ones who get away that you can''t forget.', 30, 0), (479232, 'I''m odd looking. Sometimes I think I look like a funny muppet.', 1380, 0), (479233, 'Believe it or not, I make myself laugh. Sometimes when I have thoughts or say some things that are funny, it just makes me laugh, and I don''t mind laughing at it before you guys do.', 44935, 0), (479234, 'The funny thing is people won''t let me pay for things. I''ll be in a restaurant and the manager will say, ''Oh no, it''s on the house.''', 5248, 0), (479235, 'I never expected to see the day when girls would get sunburned in the places they now do.', 1122, 0), (479236, 'It is not funny that anything else should fall down only that a man should fall down. Why do we laugh? Because it is a gravely religious matter: it is the Fall of Man. Only man can be absurd: for only man can be dignified. ', 67663, 0), (479237, 'I knew exactly what to do on Alien, it was funny.', 68428, 0), (479238, 'When you''re in the editing room, the dangerous thing is that it becomes like telling a joke again and again and again. Eventually, the joke starts to not be funny. So you have to be careful that you''re not throwing the baby out with the bath water.', 68428, 0), (479239, 'You need to be silly to be funny.', 30037, 0), (479240, 'I used to stutter really badly. Everybody thinks it''s funny. And it''s not funny. It''s not.', 17532, 0), (479241, 'We''ll love you just the way you are if you''re perfect.', 21687, 0), (479242, 'Parents are the last people on earth who ought to have children.', 4111, 0), (479243, 'As for our majority... one is enough.', 1827, 0), (479244, 'Forty for you, sixty for me. And equal partners we will be.', 17330, 0), (479245, 'When I''m being funny, I try not to offend. I don''t think much of what I''ve done has been in really ghastly taste. I don''t think I have embarrassed many people or distressed them.', 13666, 0), (479246, 'The tricky thing becomes: Do you know yourself well enough to then portray that on screen? And for me, I find that really hard. I''d rather hide behind accents and funny walks.', 67004, 0), (479247, 'From my perspective, probably women are won over by people who are sweet and respectful and courteous and kind and funny. I think those are the things that win women over.', 22856, 0), (479248, 'I''m smart and I can be really funny and interesting and I can go toe-to-toe with anybody in a conversation.', 69068, 0), (479249, 'I''ve always found it easier to be funny than to be serious.', 2253, 0), (479250, 'Who included me among the ranks of the human race?', 1254, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479251, 'The easiest time to be funny is during a fairly serious situation. That way, you can break the ice. It''s crazy, but even at funerals, people will get huge laughs.', 23202, 0), (479252, 'There''s a funny thing about fame. The truth is you run as fast as you can towards it because it''s everything you want. Not just the fame but what it represents, meaning work, meaning opportunity. And then you get there, and it''s shocking how immediately you become enveloped in this world that is incredibly restricting.', 7961, 0), (479253, 'I never smoked. I never drank and I never took drugs. The funny thing is, nothing is more boring, people like this. For me, it''s OK. But most of my friends, at least they smoke and drink.', 306, 0), (479254, 'What''s David''s role? David looks good, that''s what David does. David looks good, and I''m the funny one, that''s what I hear constantly. But I keep telling him that looks fade.', 67831, 0), (479255, 'I like Ben Stein. I think he''s funny, creative, and an insightful commentator on a host of issues.', 34704, 0), (479256, 'It may sound funny, but it''s true: I tried to put myself through the 12-step program. I didn''t want to attend a real meeting; my role didn''t really require that, and I feel those meetings are sort of sacred, and they''re anonymous for a reason. I tried to deal with some of my love of snacks - and I relapsed a lot.', 67336, 0), (479257, 'You have to discover when you''re inadequate to be funny and you don''t know you''re inadequate when you''re a kid.', 51334, 0), (479258, 'Plus, I love comic writing. Nothing satisfies me more than finding a funny way to phrase something.', 5873, 0), (479259, 'I can''t be funny if my feet don''t feel right.', 22849, 0), (479260, 'It''s funny, in a way the actor is a writer. It''s not like the two things are so separate as to be like apples and oranges. The writer and the actor are one.', 9118, 0), (479261, 'To label me an intellectual is a misunderstanding of what that is.', 12902, 0), (479262, 'It''s funny; recently I''ve started to notice people''s impersonations of me, and it''s basically like a hyperactive child.', 22301, 0), (479263, 'In my film ''Queen'', there was a funny moment with the bra. My director called and said they are blurring the bra. They said it is vulgar. Our director was furious about it. We are artistes... We see props as they are. A woman''s bra is not a danger to the society.', 67017, 0), (479264, 'I''m opening up my heart to the idea of dating. It''s funny - my friends would always come to me for romantic advice. I know nothing, and things have changed since I was dating in high school! I''m really trying hard to spend this time working on myself.', 68919, 0), (479265, 'All directors are control freaks and very obsessive. I get the feeling that directors as kids, they all have had a childhood with not too much contact with other kids. They constructed their own reality and they continue to do it. It''s a funny breed, directors.', 67649, 0), (479266, 'It''s funny as I get older I''m reverting to my roots - I want to plant stuff.', 28488, 0), (479267, 'It''s a weird thing. Rick Springfield wrote ''Jessie''s Girl,'' and he probably gets sick of talking about ''Jessie''s Girl.'' The thing is, I didn''t write ''Blurred Lines.'' I didn''t direct the music video. I''m really happy for the success, but it is kind of a funny thing to follow me around.', 67018, 0), (479268, 'I think a lot of stuff I find funny is from day dreaming.', 2315, 0), (479269, 'I think since I was kid people told me that they thought I was funny.', 2315, 0), (479270, 'I''m surrounded by friends and family who are not that impressed by celebrity. They don''t have any problem telling me I''m acting like an idiot or I''m not that funny.', 69336, 0), (479271, 'I think it''s funny to be delicate with subjects that are explosive.', 2195, 0), (479272, 'I''m a pretty funny guy, and I would love to do a comedy with a bunch of funny guys - movie-star guys, where they could help me through it.', 11158, 0), (479273, 'What''s funny is that the idea of popularity - even the use of the word ''popular'' - is something that had been mostly absent from my life since junior high. In fact, the hallmark of life after junior high seemed to be the shedding of popularity as a central concern.', 38818, 0), (479274, 'The funny thing about directing is that you have your own opinions, but it''s a collaboration. Directing is a group effort. Even though you might think something works, the smartest thing you can do as a director is try and weigh the opinions of the people around you.', 23824, 0), (479275, 'It''s funny how a chubby kid can just be having fun, and people call it entertainment!', 56259, 0), (479276, 'It''s funny, but you get to a time in your life when you think you have all the friends you will ever have.', 67563, 0), (479277, 'It''s funny because I think that both France and Britain are known for their distinctive styles, and everyone says that France is so chic and elegant but I think, more than that, French women are renowned for dressing in what suits them.', 45044, 0), (479278, 'If you imagine yourself to be someone who is very uncomfortable in their own skin, then it does funny things to your voice.', 68436, 0), (479279, 'What''s interesting about Laurel and Hardy is that in most comedy teams, there''s a straight man, and then there''s the funny guy. And with Laurel and Hardy, they''re both the funny guy.', 69344, 0), (479280, 'People say funny things all the time during really serious moments in life.', 67788, 0), (479281, 'My sister and I - she''s a musician - we jam all the time. We always play around for giggles with stuff that seem unconventional or stuff that seems funny. A lot of the stuff sometimes is just a response from jam sessions in her room, so she''ll be on the guitar or the keyboard, and we''ll just start singing and doing stuff.', 68926, 0), (479282, 'Before the Kennedys were elected, there had been older Presidents. Then here was this devastatingly attractive young couple with two beautiful children. They were so intelligent, graceful, gracious and funny. They enjoyed life so much. That''s what caught America''s eye.', 70057, 0), (479283, 'All my children inherited perfect pitch.', 67037, 0), (479284, 'Parrots make great pets. They have more personality than goldfish.', 67037, 0), (479285, 'I would love to do a movie with Albert Brooks; we''re so different, but I find him so funny, and I can be just as seemingly narcissistic as he comes off, the ''it''s all about me'' kind of thing.', 67037, 0), (479286, 'It''s funny when people say, ''I don''t think Julia likes me.'' Honey, if I don''t like you, you''re going to know about it.', 64247, 0), (479287, 'The follow your dreams thing is really important because so many people are railroaded into taking other paths by their family, their friends, people who should be supportive going, ''What are you talking about?'' Even just seemingly regular career paths, but if it''s not what people expect for you they kind of react funny.', 68442, 0), (479288, 'I have a very low level of recognition, which is fine by me.', 1479, 0), (479289, 'The first day one is a guest, the second a burden, and the third a pest.', 5879, 0), (479290, 'Do I like being thought of as attractive? I don''t know anyone on Earth who doesn''t, but I do find it funny.', 7847, 0), (479291, 'I find it very easy playing Bond. I think he''s hilarious. He gets himself into some extraordinarily funny situations.', 66678, 0), (479292, 'I mean, I - it''s so funny, I am, you know, I am, you know, a working woman out in the world, but I still live with my parents half the time. I''ve been sort of taking this very long, stuttering period of moving out.', 2250, 0), (479293, 'I never thought of myself as like, a funny person.', 2250, 0), (479294, 'It is a scientific fact that your body will not absorb cholesterol if you take it from another person''s plate.', 2223, 0), (479295, 'Life''s pretty funny when you''re objectively on the outside looking at it.', 8605, 0), (479296, 'Have enough sense to know, ahead of time, when your skills will not extend to wallpapering.', 814, 0), (479297, 'Things can be funny when people are uneasy. It softens them up and stops them falling asleep on the sofa. I like those moments where people half-smile and half-wince.', 1066, 0), (479298, 'I look at old performance videos now, and it''s really funny - I thought I was such a gangster!', 70213, 0), (479299, 'One of the funny things in life to me is a guy who takes himself very seriously.', 68444, 0), (479300, 'Every man has his follies - and often they are the most interesting thing he has got.', 3355, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479301, 'Flattery is like cologne water, to be smelt, not swallowed.', 3355, 0), (479302, 'Working for President Nixon was the most extraordinary professional experience of my life. He was endlessly fascinating: brilliant, visionary, kind, generous, warm, funny - and yes, a good man.', 68666, 0), (479303, 'I think our Batman had to be fun, light-hearted, funny, tongue-in-cheek... and I think that made kind of an homage to those earlier comic books, where Batman always had a quip or something.', 68445, 0), (479304, 'I have the curse of thinking funny!', 68445, 0), (479305, 'I''m an unorthodox type of guy, a funny guy - at least I think I''m funny. And one of the things I like to do is come up with nicknames for myself.', 66772, 0), (479306, 'It''s funny because being comedic and happy and lighthearted is who I am as a person, so they''re easier emotions for me to connect with.', 67763, 0), (479307, 'The guys on the stunt team are really fantastic. It''s really funny, because for all the aggression they have to display on screen, they''re actually really happy, good- natured people.', 68452, 0), (479308, 'It''s funny when you''re a kid how you can acclimate to almost anything.', 16775, 0), (479309, 'When I eventually met Mr. Right I had no idea that his first name was Always.', 2210, 0), (479310, 'When I was a little kid, I wrote this play about all these characters living in a haunted house. There was a witch who lived there, and a mummy. When they were all hassling him, this guy who bought the house - I can''t believe I remember this - he said to them, ''Who''s paying the mortgage on this haunted house?'' I thought that was really funny.', 1289, 0), (479311, 'I grew up in a funny way.', 49687, 0), (479312, 'It''s painful for me to watch someone who isn''t funny. It''s horrifying to sit in the back and watch some guy who just totally sucks.', 43216, 0), (479313, 'I have this weird obsession with kids and old people falling. Like, funny falls. It is awful, but it''s the thing that makes me laugh the most.', 72671, 0), (479314, 'I get called ''the girl off the dancing horse.'' I just laugh; I think it''s really funny. It''s true, isn''t it? It''s great we''re getting that recognition.', 68290, 0), (479315, 'I can speak Esperanto like a native.', 7873, 0), (479316, 'Progress was all right. Only it went on too long.', 1843, 0), (479317, 'I don''t hate humanity and I''m not interested in people who do. Although, it''s funny, actually, some of my favorite writers really do. Like Martin Amis. My dirty secret. ''London Fields'' is one of my favorite books ever. And it''s indefensible! But he''s so funny... I forgive him everything.', 20, 0), (479318, 'To be thrown onto the stand-up stage is an experience that you cannot fathom until you''re actually there, because there''s no place to go, and everyone is looking at you and you can''t even see them because of the lights. And yet you have to manage to start talking and be funny on top of it.', 68460, 0), (479319, 'But I think you can make fun of anything as long as it''s funny enough.', 18382, 0), (479320, 'I saw 28 Days. I don''t remember rehab being like a day camp or being that funny. Rehab is a dumping ground. It''s a big landfill.', 23240, 0), (479321, 'I''ve started looking at my own father a bit funny. He assures me, though, that I really am the son of a Scottish postman.', 494, 0), (479322, 'I have six locks on my door all in a row. When I go out, I lock every other one. I figure no matter how long somebody stands there picking the locks, they are always locking three.', 28346, 0), (479323, 'I don''t mean to sound - I don''t want it to come out funny, but I don''t like show business. I love - I love acting in films. I love it.', 3212, 0), (479324, 'I don''t think anyone should write their autobiography until after they''re dead.', 31112, 0), (479325, 'I read part of it all the way through.', 31112, 0), (479326, 'One man''s folly is another man''s wife.', 2362, 0), (479327, 'Acting is all about big hair and funny props... All the great actors knew it. Olivier knew it, Brando knew it.', 28896, 0), (479328, 'One of the things I like about acting is that, in a funny way, I come back to myself.', 31358, 0), (479329, 'It''s funny because I''m a sucker for glitz and glitter when it comes to clothes and nail polish, but with my makeup, I''m more comfortable with a natural look. It feels more like me.', 68292, 0), (479330, 'As soon as I realized you could be funny as a job, that was the job I wanted.', 70692, 0), (479331, 'I''m like the master of ceremonies being funny, and then sometimes people you''re with, girlfriends and stuff, are like, ''God I wish I had the person on stage to be with all the time.''', 29517, 0), (479332, 'Sometimes when you write something on the page, it can seem very funny, but when you act it out - and this happens to me a lot, actually - the melancholy of the situation becomes more front and center.', 69014, 0), (479333, 'Often, joking for me is a way of diffusing the awkwardness of a situation, so it''s kind of exhilarating to be a part of projects where there''s nothing funny or lighthearted.', 13298, 0), (479334, 'I will say this about the truth - that it''s one of those crisis rules, whether you are a client or someone who''s living their life just every day - is that the truth has a funny way of not going away, and telling the truth is extremely important in dealing with any problem or crisis.', 69516, 0), (479335, 'I joke around a lot about the manic times because they''re funny. We manics do outrageous things and it is part of our colorful nature.', 57186, 0), (479336, 'If love is the answer, could you please rephrase the question?', 1059, 0), (479337, 'Working with Chaplin was very amusing and strange. His films are so funny, but working with him, I found him to be a very serious man. Whereas the films of Hitchcock are macabre, he could be a very funny man to work with, always telling jokes and holding court. Of course, when I worked with Charlie he was getting older.', 74538, 0), (479338, 'In a funny way, poems are suited to modern life. They''re short, they''re intense. Nobody has time to read a 700-page book. People read magazines, and a poem takes less time than an article.', 10105, 0), (479339, 'I''m sure that my parents'' behavior has entered my work, I''m sorry to say. I don''t think you need to have a difficult childhood to be funny, but it helps.', 8062, 0), (479340, 'I do find comedy difficult. I don''t know why. Maybe I think about it too much. There''s a tremendous amount of pressure to be funny.', 67509, 0), (479341, 'As I get older, I just prefer to knit.', 62661, 0), (479342, 'I think serial monogamy says it all.', 62661, 0), (479343, 'The last time I saw him he was walking down lover''s lane holding his own hand.', 13077, 0), (479344, 'How many people here have telekenetic powers? Raise my hand.', 47639, 0), (479345, 'I''ve always enjoyed making people laugh. But in order for me to be funny, I have to get ticked off about something.', 2257, 0), (479346, 'Chris Hemsworth is like Christopher Reeve in that he can do two things: he can wear a big red cape without a shred of self-consciousness. But he''s also funny as hell, and he''s so sweet. So with all the fish-out-of-water stuff, he''s so funny. So he does almost two jobs in a way.', 1101, 0), (479347, 'I would call it a comedy variety show. We have some people just doing straight standup. We usually try to have one musical act of sort. So its just people being funny in different ways, not just sketch, not just standup, not just characters, all of those things.', 73216, 0), (479348, 'I''m not one to sit here and judge here. But I think it''s funny that the people that condemn the adult industry the most are the ones consuming the product the most.', 26862, 0), (479349, 'I''m somebody who believes in funny things, and laughing, but I do like for them to come from a place that addresses the human condition.', 71585, 0), (479350, 'You can''t make everybody laugh. You gotta just do what you think is funny. Just be obstreperous to everybody.', 36389, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479351, 'Whenever a film allows you to think and feel and take it beyond the moment, I think it''s achieved something. And ''Funny Games'' does that.', 67575, 0), (479352, 'I started writing when I was 9 years old. I was like this weird kid who would just stay in my room, typing little funny magazines and drawing comic strips.', 20136, 0), (479353, 'The magic in performing as an entertaining ventriloquist happens when the characters come to life and the interaction between the separate personalities on stage becomes ''real.'' Then don''t forget that the act has to be funny, and to me, being funny and entertaining any given audience is more important than anything.', 13245, 0), (479354, 'I''ve always said that instead of watching a guy juggle seven things amazingly I would rather see a really bad juggler who''s really funny.', 13245, 0), (479355, 'I''m one of those hovering mothers and I know it''s really important to have an independent child, so I''m trying to back off, but it''s hard. I love him so much, and he''s so funny and cute to me.', 68505, 0), (479356, 'It''s funny, but to me, when you go to a concert hall and hear electronic pieces from the ''60s, I think they sound really dated. But when an orchestra plays a piece from that period, and it''s going to sound different every time, it feels more modern to me.', 71752, 0), (479357, 'I''m good at coming up with wacky characters and funny dialogue.', 68400, 0), (479358, 'How can you analyse what is funny? What''s funny to one isn''t funny to another... What''s funny to you is a personal thing.', 64396, 0), (479359, 'I''m doing a pilot for Comedy Central with the band Steel Panther. They''re faux heavy metal. They started as kind of a tribute band out here, or a cover band, and they''re funny guys, and they just sort of morphed into their own thing.', 70287, 0), (479360, 'What you do with it and things like that, but I basically chose this after I read it because I thought it was different and funny and unique and dark - things that I like to do.', 68298, 0), (479361, 'I sang in the choir for years, even though my family belonged to another church.', 70649, 0), (479362, 'I wish I had the nerve not to tip.', 70649, 0), (479363, 'I don''t know who the hell Paul Lynde is, or why he''s funny, and I prefer it to be a mystery to me.', 70649, 0), (479364, 'I realized I was gay in the shower one day with Barbra Streisand. It happened while I was lathering, rinsing, and repeating with Pert Plus. As I was belting out the chorus to my favorite song from ''Funny Girl,'' ''Oh my man, I love him so, he''ll never know...'' it hit me.', 69039, 0), (479365, 'It''s funny, because I did all of these interviews as soon as I had the baby, and they were asking questions, and I really didn''t have an idea of anything, because I was so blurry.', 66811, 0), (479366, 'I''ve never gotten to do romantic comedy like most of the girls. Maybe because I''m fit, people assume that I''m not funny?', 69216, 0), (479367, 'Yes, I believe blue material is funny, but if that''s all you''ve got, you''re dead in the water. It''s not good.', 45613, 0), (479368, 'I grew up in Europe, where the history comes from.', 2246, 0), (479369, 'I mean, sometimes... a comedian becomes an actor, and they just don''t deliver, because the bottom line of comedy is to be funny, and the bottom line of acting is to be truthful, and they get that mixed up sometimes, or don''t even notice that that''s the thing.', 2246, 0), (479370, 'It''s a funny relationship that makeup artists have. I always feel kind of like a dentist. People look at me and think of pain.', 74956, 0), (479371, 'Sometimes I am so dry that people don''t know I''m kidding and think I''m being serious. I enjoy this because their reactions are often funny.', 34807, 0), (479372, 'I don''t have a bank account because I don''t know my mother''s maiden name.', 6225, 0), (479373, 'I''m kidding about having only a few dollars. I might have a few dollars more.', 22838, 0), (479374, 'There''s something that''s really fun about the challenge of making the mundane funny, too, I think.', 13056, 0), (479375, 'It all started when my dog began getting free roll over minutes.', 46197, 0), (479376, 'I recorded my hair this morning, tonight I''m watching the highlights.', 46197, 0), (479377, 'I realised that if you get yourself labeled as the funny one, people don''t look any further. I''ve used that as I''ve got older. It''s controlling: I decide what part of my personality you''re seeing. I don''t want you to look at me, I really don''t. I don''t want you to comment on my clothes, my hair or the way I look.', 58382, 0), (479378, 'You know, I''m just a very boring, not very funny person in person. I don''t feel pressured to be otherwise.', 339, 0), (479379, 'The best measure of a man''s honesty isn''t his income tax return. It''s the zero adjust on his bathroom scale.', 1004, 0), (479380, 'Also, in a funny way, if you have been happily married there are no unresolved areas, nothing to prove to yourself after the other dies.', 44007, 0), (479381, 'I remember watching Gilda Radner when I was a kid and everyone thought she was so funny and no one ever said that she was a funny woman, she was just funny.', 68540, 0), (479382, 'Jon Stewart hires people that he thinks are funny. That''s it. That''s the only requirement.', 68545, 0), (479383, 'They''re great girls. They''re very funny, they''re very smart, they''re fun to be with. They''re very lively, as I think people can tell. And you know, they''re very confident girls.', 11480, 0), (479384, 'What''s funny about the slacker thing, people project an image of what they think a musician is: young, slack, unemployed - like a really romantic idea of a poet, writer or musician - which isn''t really true a lot of the time. I don''t reckon you would know anything about me if I wasn''t moderately hard-working.', 70306, 0), (479385, 'It is to be observed that ''angling'' is the name given to fishing by people who can''t fish.', 9981, 0), (479386, 'It''s so funny, because when I was growing up in a small town in New Hampshire, I was obsessed with Leonardo DiCaprio - from the ''Growing Pains''/''What''s Eating Gilbert Grape'' era, because he was superhot - and I carried a laminated photo of him in my wallet and said he was my boyfriend. But no one believed me.', 68549, 0), (479387, '''Thunderbolts'' I was mostly attracted to because I really wanted to write Punisher and Elektra and Deadpool, who are characters I have always really enjoyed. But the funny thing is that over time, I came to really like Red Leader; he became one of my favorite guys in the book. Sometimes characters surprise you.', 69391, 0), (479388, 'And remember, it''s also very funny, because side by side with grief lies joy.', 34619, 0), (479389, 'If you have a secret, people will sit a little bit closer.', 69393, 0), (479390, 'Communism is like one big phone company.', 2212, 0), (479391, 'I remember nearly having a fit of the giggles during the reading because dear Daniel was SO respectful and serious and I was finding the whole situation funny because I was speaking to his profile.', 68554, 0), (479392, 'It''s funny, after a while, you get tired of having to fight someone because they don''t like the way you look.', 73676, 0), (479393, 'I like to make jokes I consider myself a funny person. I just think making jokes about people who are in a situation beyond their control is not funny to them or their families.', 32356, 0), (479394, 'And at the time, it is funny how you can look at something and say, for example with my shoulder injury, when it first happened I said this is the worst thing that could happen to me. Why me, why now? Now I look back and say it was probably the best thing that happened to me.', 53870, 0), (479395, 'What was really funny is that as I got older all those guys who called me a sissy in junior high school wanted me to be their best friend because they wanted to meet all the girls that I knew in figure skating.', 33916, 0), (479396, 'Usually, if I think something is really funny, I''m not gonna test it. I''ll just test it when I''m onstage.', 20007, 0), (479397, 'It''s so funny because I listen to songs that I recorded that I didn''t really know anything about at the time. Later on I''m starting to feel the songs. Sing them first, feel them later.', 70320, 0), (479398, 'Everybody''s funny if you love them.', 74957, 0), (479399, 'I like the hot-cold, the sugar-salt, being able to play over-the-top and dramatic things - in the same film. Just as in my life, I can be very funny and at other times almost extinguished.', 72258, 0), (479400, 'Comedians don''t laugh. They''re too busy analyzing why it''s funny or not.', 66132, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479401, 'Whenever I''m in the U.K., people say I have an American accent. Which is, obviously, funny.', 74958, 0), (479402, 'It''s funny to think that when you get done with an acting job, you''re considered unemployed. There are definitely times when those checks don''t last forever. I went to college at a private school, and I racked up quite a bit of debt. I was very slow to pay them back.', 71113, 0), (479403, 'Snoop Dogg is hilarious. T.I. is really funny. Who else? 50 Cent is hilarious. Jay-Z is funny. I''ve met him, but he''s funny in interviews. He was funny when I saw him, too. Ludacris is funny. Everybody is. Rappers are funny, a lot of them.', 73237, 0), (479404, 'I like to tell kids that I started thinking about stories when I first started reading stuff like Dr. Seuss and ''Go, Dog. Go!,'' thinking, ''Oh yeah, that''s funny. I''d like to do that.'' And then writing throughout school, but at the same time I was studying pre-med stuff, because my mom told me I should be a doctor.', 2214, 0), (479405, 'The way taxes are, you might as well marry for love.', 63346, 0), (479406, 'I really love showing up at work at 10 A.M., trying to make it funny until 3 P.M., and then going home. It''s like comedy bankers'' hours.', 74959, 0), (479407, 'I live in a wonderful world of make-believe. A world of Ginger Rogers and Fred Astaire. A world of Winnie the Pooh and Edward Bear. Things like that. Wonderful things. Funny things.', 74960, 0), (479408, 'What does being a woman today mean? Is there a right way of doing it? Is there a wrong way of doing it? Different kinds of women, female friendships: It''s all pretty funny, and worth making fun of.', 74961, 0), (479409, 'Whoever is my relative, I will not be nice to them.', 72834, 0), (479410, 'It''s a funny business. I kind of compare it to baseball. I''m always looking for a home run.', 72942, 0), (479411, 'For sheer sexiness, a man must be beautiful. Funny. yes. Clever, no.', 70860, 0), (479412, 'I''d so much rather people think I was funny than pretty.', 51527, 0), (479413, 'The heroines in ''That''s What She Said'' are flawed, messy, damaged, hilarious and culpable and not really concerned about being acceptable to the audience in any traditional sense, which for me is what makes them all the more gorgeous. And the fearless truth of that is what makes it funny.', 68596, 0), (479414, 'It''s really irritating. Even people who like my work sometimes come up to me and say, ''I usually don''t like female comedians, but your material is great!'' It makes the job prospect more daunting. Funny is funny, you know?', 74962, 0), (479415, 'Someone told me that when they go to Vermont, they feel like they''re home. I''m that way at Saks.', 62986, 0), (479416, 'It''s funny because I remember when I came to the U.S. with ''Swimming Pool,'' the movie did well, and it was great box office for a French movie, but I remember I was a bit upset because all people talked to me about was the nudity.', 74963, 0), (479417, 'But I believe that there are marriages where you can have your pool table and she can have her scrapbooking room or garden or whatever it is. But when everyone has what they want, it''s not funny. There''s no conflict.', 68619, 0), (479418, 'I own and operate a ferocious ego.', 4793, 0), (479419, 'I read a funny story about how the Republicans freed the slaves. The Republicans are the ones who created slavery by law in the 1600''s. Abraham Lincoln freed the slaves and he was not a Republican.', 49158, 0), (479420, 'Until you walk a mile in another man''s moccasins you can''t imagine the smell.', 2350, 0), (479421, 'The drawings in ''Portal'' were actually me scribbling that stuff... I had a funny moment when I realized that someone gotten ''The cake is a lie'' tattooed on themselves. It was really interesting to see my handwriting tattooed on another human being. That... that''s odd.', 74964, 0), (479422, 'My mother was a terrific force in my life. Wartime-generation woman, hadn''t gone to university but should have done. Was very funny, very verbal, very clever, very witty.', 74965, 0), (479423, 'I''m too busy thinking what I''m going to say next to remember what I''ve said, but my staff tells me I''m sometimes funny. Not always on purpose, though.', 74966, 0), (479424, 'I quit therapy because my analyst was trying to help me behind my back.', 68415, 0), (479425, 'When you''re in love it''s the most glorious two and a half days of your life.', 68415, 0), (479426, 'Dad was the first man I fell in love with. He was a very funny man. He grew up in the East End of London and was very dynamic, and I understood why my mother fell in love with him.', 74366, 0), (479427, 'I can play a cat lady. I can''t put my foot down and refuse to play anything but playing the perfect, well-adjusted woman, because those people aren''t as fun or funny.', 74967, 0), (479428, 'My dad was in the army so we moved around a lot and I changed schools every year and had to make new friends, and I found that if I was the funny guy I could do that easier.', 40154, 0), (479429, 'If the worst that happens is that I wake up and see a picture of myself and a headline saying, ''He wasn''t very funny last night'', then I''ve got nothing to complain about.', 74267, 0), (479430, 'I''m a misplaced American, but don''t know where I was misplaced.', 22209, 0), (479431, 'When somebody listens and laughs, you''re always in better shape than when you''re with those folks who just kind of look at you when you say something funny. You wonder if they''re looking at you because they''re mad that they didn''t say it or something. It''s hard to handle that.', 74968, 0), (479432, 'I think it''s great when dramatic actors do lighter, funny roles.', 72694, 0), (479433, 'When I have had a long day at work, I want something to watch that is funny, lighthearted and easy to get into, and reality is that. I''m not really into serious programmes or documentaries.', 74969, 0), (479434, 'There''s one thing about baldness, it''s neat.', 21321, 0), (479435, 'It''s funny, because I''ve never thought of myself as a Hispanic actor, like in ''American Gangster,'' I''m playing an Italian. I''ve always been fortunate enough to have been allowed to play all these diverse roles.', 74970, 0), (479436, 'I don''t believe that anybody has come to a conclusion on why something is funny. It''s funny because it''s ridiculous and it''s ridiculous for different reasons at different times.', 23103, 0), (479437, 'If at first you don''t succeed, blame your parents.', 63122, 0), (479438, 'Possibly I''ve become less funny as I''ve been happier.', 8761, 0), (479439, 'Working with Julie Andrews is like getting hit over the head with a valentine.', 70154, 0), (479440, 'My parents are both really, really funny, and my little sister is a really good painter, and my other sister is a really good writer.', 74971, 0), (479441, 'Fencing is a funny sport. Competitive fencing is not really very applicable to the stage world unless you''re fighting with a rapier during the Renaissance, you know?', 74972, 0), (479442, 'Girls don''t poop, so don''t claim you do. You can fart - because farting is funny - but we don''t want to know that you poop.', 74973, 0), (479443, 'I''ve played a ghost, cat, snake. I''ve been funny, sad. I''ve been filmed flying on screen. So why not spend time on something else? I don''t need to accept everything I''m offered.', 74974, 0), (479444, 'It''s funny how getting older - or being overlooked and underrated for more than two decades - can make you change your ambitions.', 74975, 0), (479445, 'I''m a classic example of all humorists - only funny when I''m working.', 37941, 0), (479446, 'We know that the nature of genius is to provide idiots with ideas twenty years later.', 16839, 0), (479447, 'When I was born I owed twelve dollars.', 53400, 0), (479448, 'It''s a funny thing, but today the Titanic is probably much more - that is people are much more aware of it than they were in 1954, when I was doing my research.', 55949, 0), (479449, 'Porsche is a driver''s car - a performance car. That was funny - here''s this awesome car, but it''s got no cup holders.', 74976, 0), (479450, 'I don''t think I was funny until college. I lived with some Harvard MD/PhD students - they were so smart, and what I contributed to the house was, I was the funny one.', 27946, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479451, 'Violence is not funny.', 69474, 0), (479452, 'I''m not a person who can spontaneously say funny things.', 74977, 0), (479453, 'It''s kind of a funny way to put it, but if you want to study a dynamic economic system, what you''d like to be able to do is focus on the linkages, say, between asset markets and the macro economy without having to model everything at the same time.', 74978, 0), (479454, 'It was Nick Willing''s intention to make ''Hatter'' as sarcastically British funny as he could.', 74979, 0), (479455, 'I really think that sex always looks kind of funny in a movie.', 69474, 0), (479456, 'I don''t get offered many dramatic roles. As soon as my face pops up in a movie, everyone knows I''m the funny guy.', 74980, 0), (479457, 'After all is said and done, sit down.', 37846, 0), (479458, 'When I go to a bar, I don''t go looking for a girl who knows the capital of Maine.', 74932, 0), (479459, 'I don''t know, I feel like any role that I play is a little piece of me, whether it''s their perspective, maybe how they dress, what they think is funny, their loyalty to their friends. It all stems from Kiersey.', 74981, 0), (479460, 'Losing streaks are funny. If you lose at the beginning you got off to a bad start. If you lose in the middle of the season, you''re in a slump. If you lose at the end, you''re choking.', 74982, 0), (479461, 'I''ve played villains on stage - you know, the Iagos and so on - but I think of myself as a funny person. I mostly did comedies before I did TV work.', 74983, 0), (479462, 'Being funny has always mattered a lot to me. It''s why I started acting - to make my friends laugh.', 74822, 0), (479463, 'I''ve been lucky enough to play some funny, nasty ladies in my day, and if you can make them foolish, they''re even funnier.', 74984, 0), (479464, 'I just write what I think is funny. I don''t care who watches it.', 74985, 0), (479465, 'If I could play any role in any musical, it would be Desiree in ''A Little Night Music'' - Oh my, it is perfection. The character gets to be funny, beautiful, sexy and smart all at the same time and have two men fighting over her. The show is Stephen Sondheim at his absolute best... need I say more?', 74986, 0), (479466, 'The three theater peeps I would love to dine with are Mel Brooks, because he is so funny; Stephen Sondheim, because he is a god-like genius; and Ethel Merman, to compare notes on fabulous belting.', 74986, 0), (479467, 'It''s funny, the moment you dread the most, seeing yourself bald, is actually not such a bad moment at all.', 70226, 0), (479468, 'It''s a grim business, this being funny. Every time you come up with a strong, satiric idea, the world tops it.', 74365, 0), (479469, 'It just so happens that people aren''t doing comedy about abortion or cannibalism or waterboarding. And that to me doesn''t necessarily mean that there aren''t aspects of those subjects that are funny, it just means that people are too uptight.', 74987, 0), (479470, 'You know my girls are so funny. You''re out in the country and there are critters everywhere and they get a little like, ''Oh my God! Oh no, bugs!'' and I had to say, ''Honey this is fine. This is their world and it''s all part of being in the country.'' I realized, ''Oh my God, my girls are really city girls.''', 74988, 0), (479471, 'Unfortunately, sometimes the fans forget who puts the money and passion into the club. It''s funny, but when you win, it''s the coach and the players who are responsible, but when you lose, it''s the owner''s fault; but that''s football.', 74989, 0), (479472, 'One of the funny things of being a producer, you have these fleeting, intense relationships with people, and they go off to global megastardom, and you don''t see them.', 74990, 0), (479473, 'Let''s make some funny pictures.', 74991, 0), (479474, 'In all my years as an actor, I had never been me - I had always hidden behind my glasses, mustaches and funny voices.', 74992, 0), (479475, 'Logic will get you from A to B. Imagination will take you everywhere.', 104, 0), (479476, 'This world is but a canvas to our imagination.', 1049, 0), (479477, 'They who dream by day are cognizant of many things which escape those who dream only by night.', 49, 0), (479478, 'Every block of stone has a statue inside it and it is the task of the sculptor to discover it.', 12364, 0), (479479, 'When you''re curious, you find lots of interesting things to do.', 65266, 0), (479480, 'The only limit to your impact is your imagination and commitment.', 5675, 0), (479481, 'Passion is what gives meaning to our lives. It''s what allows us to achieve success beyond our wildest imagination. Try to find a career path that you have a passion for.', 74701, 0), (479482, 'The world of reality has its limits the world of imagination is boundless.', 1372, 0), (479483, 'The English language is nobody''s special property. It is the property of the imagination: it is the property of the language itself.', 5030, 0), (479484, 'Girls are capable of doing everything men are capable of doing. Sometimes they have more imagination than men.', 70564, 0), (479485, 'You''re only given a little spark of madness. You mustn''t lose it.', 2185, 0), (479486, 'We are more often frightened than hurt and we suffer more from imagination than from reality.', 65434, 0), (479487, 'Each generation imagines itself to be more intelligent than the one that went before it, and wiser than the one that comes after it.', 521, 0), (479488, 'I saw the angel in the marble and carved until I set him free.', 12364, 0), (479489, 'Imagination will often carry us to worlds that never were. But without it we go nowhere.', 133, 0), (479490, 'I like nonsense it wakes up the brain cells.', 3, 0), (479491, 'Visualize this thing that you want, see it, feel it, believe in it. Make your mental blue print, and begin to build.', 10101, 0), (479492, 'The level of our success is limited only by our imagination and no act of kindness, however small, is ever wasted.', 1733, 0), (479493, 'The ability to recognize opportunities and move in new - and sometimes unexpected - directions will benefit you no matter your interests or aspirations. A liberal arts education is designed to equip students for just such flexibility and imagination.', 13632, 0), (479494, 'Imagination and fiction make up more than three quarters of our real life.', 1662, 0), (479495, 'If you want a vision of the future, imagine a boot stamping on a human face - forever.', 521, 0), (479496, 'If you can imagine it, you can achieve it. If you can dream it, you can become it.', 1820, 0), (479497, 'The visionary starts with a clean sheet of paper, and re-imagines the world.', 1833, 0), (479498, 'I do not stick to rules when cooking. I rely on my imagination.', 67344, 0), (479499, 'Imagination is the highest kite one can fly.', 12702, 0), (479500, 'My imagination is a monastery and I am its monk.', 191, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479501, 'I cannot imagine a God who rewards and punishes the objects of his creation and is but a reflection of human frailty.', 104, 0), (479502, 'I love to create, and to me, the ultimate freedom of expression is a blank canvas or a block of clay to capture whatever emotions your imagination gives it.', 68041, 0), (479503, 'I have fallen in love with the imagination. And if you fall in love with the imagination, you understand that it is a free spirit. It will go anywhere, and it can do anything.', 753, 0), (479504, 'To bring anything into your life, imagine that it''s already there.', 424, 0), (479505, 'Imagination is the only key to the future. Without it none exists - with it all things are possible.', 65659, 0), (479506, 'There are two worlds: the world we can measure with line and rule, and the world that we feel with our hearts and imagination.', 840, 0), (479507, 'Be bored and see where it takes you, because the imagination''s dusty wilderness is worth crossing if you want to sculpt your soul.', 36805, 0), (479508, 'I paint objects as I think them, not as I see them.', 981, 0), (479509, 'The imagination is the golden pathway to everywhere.', 1106, 0), (479510, 'With the brush we merely tint, while the imagination alone produces colour.', 74993, 0), (479511, 'Imagination rules the world.', 1702, 0), (479512, 'Lyrically I like to use themes that make the listener use his or her imagination, and to give a little of the lessons I''ve learned in my own life.', 27500, 0), (479513, 'Formulate and stamp indelibly on your mind a mental picture of yourself as succeeding. Hold this picture tenaciously. Never permit it to fade. Your mind will seek to develop the picture... Do not build up obstacles in your imagination.', 1699, 0), (479514, 'Those who have learned to walk on the threshold of the unknown worlds, by means of what are commonly termed par excellence the exact sciences, may then, with the fair white wings of imagination, hope to soar further into the unexplored amidst which we live.', 70815, 0), (479515, 'What we wish, we readily believe, and what we ourselves think, we imagine others think also.', 62623, 0), (479516, 'Where there is no imagination there is no horror.', 764, 0), (479517, 'When you believe in what you''re doing and use your imagination and initiative, you can make a difference.', 71143, 0), (479518, 'I always imagined I could be what I wanted to be.', 55068, 0), (479519, 'You have to really use your imagination to refresh your daily life.', 6421, 0), (479520, 'Our world faces a true planetary emergency. I know the phrase sounds shrill, and I know it''s a challenge to the moral imagination.', 13473, 0), (479521, 'Imagination is the real and eternal world of which this vegetable universe is but a faint shadow.', 221, 0), (479522, 'Now it is quite clear to me that there are no solid spheres in the heavens, and those that have been devised by the authors to save the appearances, exist only in the imagination.', 24935, 0), (479523, 'All the breaks you need in life wait within your imagination, Imagination is the workshop of your mind, capable of turning mind energy into accomplishment and wealth.', 1187, 0), (479524, 'I did spend a lot of time as a child very confused about whether I had a devil in me, or whether I was in a state of grace. I mean, these ideas are so potent to anybody with half an imagination.', 68029, 0), (479525, 'Man lives by imagination.', 62533, 0), (479526, 'You can understand nothing about art, particularly modern art, if you do not understand that imagination is a value in itself.', 61, 0), (479527, 'Technology, like art, is a soaring exercise of the human imagination.', 42473, 0), (479528, 'We say God and the imagination are one... How high that highest candle lights the dark.', 2547, 0), (479529, 'Begin noticing and being careful about keeping your imagination free of thoughts that you do not wish to materialize. Instead, initiate a practice of filling your creative thoughts to overflow with ideas and wishes that you fully intend to manifest. Honor your imaginings regardless of others seeing them as crazy or impossible.', 21729, 0), (479530, 'The saddest thing I can imagine is to get used to luxury.', 454, 0), (479531, 'I''ve got quite a vivid imagination and I''m easily overwhelmed by sensations and things that are beautiful or scary. I don''t think I''ve ever seen a ghost - I think I''m probably haunted by my own ghosts than real ones.', 22790, 0), (479532, 'Love doesn''t grow on trees like apples in Eden - it''s something you have to make. And you must use your imagination too.', 3449, 0), (479533, 'Generally speaking, a howling wilderness does not howl: it is the imagination of the traveler that does the howling.', 1049, 0), (479534, 'Illustrations can be a big window: a looking glass into the author''s imagination.', 26266, 0), (479535, 'Fantasy has a dark side to it. It also has a light hemisphere - the power of the human imagination to keep going, to imagine a better tomorrow.', 3159, 0), (479536, 'Be drawn to the visual arts for it can expand your imagination.', 74994, 0), (479537, 'My imagination is a twisted place.', 100, 0), (479538, 'Wherever you write is supposed to be a little bit of a refuge, a place where you can get away from the world. The more closed in you are, the more you''re forced back on your own imagination.', 578, 0), (479539, 'True change takes place in the imagination.', 1471, 0), (479540, 'From the boys'' point of view, scouting puts them into fraternity-gangs, which is their natural organisation, whether for games, mischief, or loafing; it gives them a smart dress and equipments; it appeals to their imagination and romance; and it engages them in an active, open-air life.', 36714, 0), (479541, 'Men are mortal. So are ideas. An idea needs propagation as much as a plant needs watering. Otherwise both will wither and die.', 5224, 0), (479542, 'It takes a lot of imagination to be a good photographer. You need less imagination to be a painter because you can invent things. But in photography everything is so ordinary it takes a lot of looking before you learn to see the extraordinary. ', 56730, 0), (479543, 'Musicals are, by nature, theatrical, meaning poetic, meaning having to move the audience''s imagination and create a suspension of disbelief, by which I mean there''s no fourth wall.', 8708, 0), (479544, 'Make sure you visualize what you really want, not what someone else wants for you.', 74995, 0), (479545, 'It is all very well to copy what one sees, but it is far better to draw what one now only sees in one''s memory. That is a transformation in which imagination collaborates with memory.', 19723, 0), (479546, 'True originality consists not in a new manner but in a new vision.', 426, 0), (479547, 'I accept that there may be things far grander and more incomprehensible than we can possibly imagine.', 1716, 0), (479548, 'Being an actor is the loneliest thing in the world. You are all alone with your concentration and imagination, and that''s all you have.', 1784, 0), (479549, 'I''m an optimistic guy. I''m one of those big dreamers. I''m one of those kids with that annoying imagination.', 19593, 0), (479550, 'Justice is to be found only in imagination.', 31009, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479551, 'Reason clears and plants the wilderness of the imagination to harvest the wheat of art.', 36106, 0), (479552, 'The Chinese art world does not exist. In a society that restricts individual freedoms and violates human rights, anything that calls itself creative or independent is a pretence. It is impossible for a totalitarian society to create anything with passion and imagination.', 20064, 0), (479553, 'I want to reach the heights of stardom beyond my imagination.', 67630, 0), (479554, 'My imagination makes me human and makes me a fool; it gives me all the world, and exiles me from it.', 77, 0), (479555, 'Anyone who said he wasn''t afraid during the civil rights movement was either a liar or without imagination. I was scared all the time. My hands didn''t shake but inside I was shaking.', 73549, 0), (479556, 'Fantasy mirrors desire. Imagination reshapes it.', 12469, 0), (479557, 'My life has been a gift up to this point, and I''ve been blessed beyond my wildest imagination. And wherever this ride takes me is where I''m going.', 16837, 0), (479558, 'The imagination is a muscle. If it is not exercised, it atrophies.', 14, 0), (479559, 'I think artists can influence only through making music that challenges people, excites them and flips them out. Music that repeats what you know in ever-decreasing derivation, that''s unchallenging and unstimulating, deadens our minds, our imagination and our ability to see beyond the hell we find ourselves in.', 70078, 0), (479560, 'Imagination is a very potent thing, and in the uneducated often usurps the place of genuine experience.', 1060, 0), (479561, 'Proficiency in a craft is essential to every artist. Therein lies the prime source of creative imagination. Let us then create a new guild of craftsmen without the class distinctions that raise an arrogant barrier between craftsman and artist!', 10311, 0), (479562, 'If you''re not a daydreamer, you haven''t got any imagination.', 70631, 0), (479563, 'My experience of great storytelling, working with classics, is just finding a way to present it simply but let the story do its own work, or be an invite to the audience''s imagination.', 63679, 0), (479564, 'I don''t like this idea of Method. I come from that school, but what I was taught was that it''s your imagination. You do your homework, and you use your imagination.', 67788, 0), (479565, 'One thing about ''Star Wars'' that I''m really proud of is that it expands the imagination. That''s why I like the ''Star Wars'' toys.', 1110, 0), (479566, 'I discovered that my imagination came alive when I moved away from the immediate world around me.', 458, 0), (479567, 'To me, it''s far more efficient to mobilize the imagination. It''s far more efficient to hear a creaking step, for example, than to see the face of a monster, which usually looks ridiculous, and where you know that the blood is ketchup.', 35830, 0), (479568, 'My reality needs imagination like a bulb needs a socket. My imagination needs reality like a blind man needs a cane.', 2201, 0), (479569, 'In rising financial markets, the world is forever new. The bull or optimist has no eyes for past or present, but only for the future, where streams of revenue play in his imagination.', 68800, 0), (479570, 'The difference between the Parthenon and the World Trade Center, between a French wine glass and a German beer mug, between Bach and John Philip Sousa, between Sophocles and Shakespeare, between a bicycle and a horse, though explicable by historical moment, necessity, and destiny, is before all a difference of imagination.', 34378, 0), (479571, 'Imagination creates reality.', 4756, 0), (479572, 'If you got a good imagination, a lot of confidence and you kind of know what you are saying, then you might be able to do it. I know a lot of colorful characters at home that would make great actors.', 68421, 0), (479573, 'I''ve learned that borders are where the actual ends, but also where the imagination and the story begins.', 68264, 0), (479574, 'It may easily come to pass that a vain man may become proud and imagine himself pleasing to all when he is in reality a universal nuisance.', 2478, 0), (479575, 'Do not quench your inspiration and your imagination do not become the slave of your model.', 89, 0), (479576, 'An opera begins long before the curtain goes up and ends long after it has come down. It starts in my imagination, it becomes my life, and it stays part of my life long after I''ve left the opera house.', 19739, 0), (479577, 'Imagine for yourself a character, a model personality, whose example you determine to follow, in private as well as in public.', 1328, 0), (479578, 'Imagination was given to man to compensate him for what he is not a sense of humor to console him for what he is.', 1035, 0), (479579, 'To imagine is everything, to know is nothing at all.', 348, 0), (479580, 'I imagine that yes is the only living thing.', 37, 0), (479581, 'An idea is salvation by imagination.', 1836, 0), (479582, 'It is impossible to imagine the universe run by a wise, just and omnipotent God, but it is quite easy to imagine it run by a board of gods.', 411, 0), (479583, 'He who does not think much of himself is much more esteemed than he imagines.', 282, 0), (479584, 'Imagination is the eye of the soul.', 8895, 0), (479585, 'I imagine, therefore I belong and am free.', 6034, 0), (479586, 'It is the eye of ignorance that assigns a fixed and unchangeable color to every object beware of this stumbling block.', 1948, 0), (479587, 'The artist must bow to the monster of his own imagination.', 2905, 0), (479588, 'The most imaginative people are the most credulous, for them everything is possible.', 58721, 0), (479589, 'You can''t do it unless you can imagine it.', 1110, 0), (479590, 'Imagination has brought mankind through the dark ages to its present state of civilization. Imagination led Columbus to discover America. Imagination led Franklin to discover electricity.', 1829, 0), (479591, 'Imagination is the voice of daring. If there is anything Godlike about God it is that. He dared to imagine everything.', 497, 0), (479592, 'I visualize things in my mind before I have to do them. It''s like having a mental workshop.', 58444, 0), (479593, 'When you can imagine you begin to create and when you begin to create you realize that you can create a world that you prefer to live in, rather than a world that you''re suffering in.', 1028, 0), (479594, 'Imagination and invention go hand in hand. Remember how lack of resources was never a problem in childhood games? Shift a few pieces of furniture around the living room, and you have yourself a fort.', 467, 0), (479595, 'Apathy can be overcome by enthusiasm, and enthusiasm can only be aroused by two things: first, an ideal, with takes the imagination by storm, and second, a definite intelligible plan for carrying that ideal into practice.', 63443, 0), (479596, 'The debt we owe to the play of imagination is incalculable.', 28934, 0), (479597, 'There are moments when a man''s imagination, so easily subdued to what it lives in, suddenly rises above its daily level and surveys the long windings of destiny.', 426, 0), (479598, 'Never lose sight of the fact that all human felicity lies in man''s imagination, and that he cannot think to attain it unless he heeds all his caprices. The most fortunate of persons is he who has the most means to satisfy his vagaries.', 2459, 0), (479599, 'That neither our thoughts, nor passions, nor ideas formed by the imagination, exist without the mind, is what every body will allow.', 43455, 0), (479600, 'However my parents - both of whom came from impoverished backgrounds and neither of whom had been to college, took the view that my overactive imagination was an amusing quirk that would never pay a mortgage or secure a pension.', 28, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479601, 'I love costumes. I love getting dressed up because it really helps my imagination make the leap to believe that I am who I say I am.', 71886, 0), (479602, 'Perhaps our imagination needs crime stories to fulfill some craving we have, as a way to assuage a darkness in ourselves.', 68918, 0), (479603, 'I had a very happy childhood, but I still used my imagination as a leisure resort.', 21955, 0), (479604, 'I must confess that my imagination refuses to see any sort of submarine doing anything but suffocating its crew and floundering at sea.', 3173, 0), (479605, 'This is one of those cases in which the imagination is baffled by the facts.', 2485, 0), (479606, 'Nothing is more fearful than imagination without taste.', 282, 0), (479607, 'Imagination allows us to escape the predictable. It enables us to reply to the common wisdom that we cannot soar by saying, ''Just watch!''', 65802, 0), (479608, 'Having imagination it takes you an hour to write a paragraph that if you were unimaginative would take you only a minute.', 62649, 0), (479609, 'The great instrument of moral good is the imagination.', 165, 0), (479610, 'Talent, lying in the understanding, is often inherited; genius, being the action of reason or imagination, rarely or never.', 1910, 0), (479611, 'Vision - It reaches beyond the thing that is, into the conception of what can be. Imagination gives you the picture. Vision gives you the impulse to make the picture your own.', 10101, 0), (479612, 'Censorship is never over for those who have experienced it. It is a brand on the imagination that affects the individual who has suffered it, forever.', 1955, 0), (479613, 'I don''t think art is propaganda; it should be something that liberates the soul, provokes the imagination and encourages people to go further. It celebrates humanity instead of manipulating it.', 19934, 0), (479614, 'What I love most about animation is, it''s a team sport, and everything we do is about pure imagination.', 71341, 0), (479615, 'You will certainly not doubt the necessity of studying astronomy and physics, if you are desirous of comprehending the relation between the world and Providence as it is in reality, and not according to imagination.', 1858, 0), (479616, 'My identity is linked to my grandmother, who''s pure Filipino, as pure as you can probably get. And that shaped my imagination. So that''s how I identify.', 68615, 0), (479617, 'In imagination, there''s no limitation.', 68089, 0), (479618, 'It always amuses me that the biggest praise for my work comes for the imagination, while the truth is that there''s not a single line in all my work that does not have a basis in reality. The problem is that Caribbean reality resembles the wildest imagination.', 183, 0), (479619, 'The thing that most attracts me to historical fiction is taking the factual record as far as it is known, using that as scaffolding, and then letting imagination build the structure that fills in those things we can never find out for sure.', 10676, 0), (479620, 'Literature is a beautiful way of keeping the imagination alive, of visiting worlds you would never have time to in your day-to-day life. It keeps you abreast of a wider spectrum of human activities.', 1458, 0), (479621, 'We need to be politically engaged, but peculiar in how we engage. Jesus and the early Christians had a marvelous political imagination. They turned all the presumptions and ideas of power and blessing upside down.', 1907, 0), (479622, 'From stoplights to skyscrapers, turn anywhere in civilization and you will see imagination at work. It''s in our inventions, advances and remedies and how a single parent masterminds each day. Imagination is boundless, surrounds us and resides in us all.', 69956, 0), (479623, 'Cinema is a world of imagination.', 2030, 0), (479624, 'America gave the world the notion of the melting pot - an alchemical cooking device wherein diverse ethnic and religious groups voluntarily mix together, producing a new, American identity. And while critics may argue that the melting pot is a national myth, it has tenaciously informed the America''s collective imagination.', 74768, 0), (479625, 'Anything you put your mind to and add your imagination into can make your life a lot better and a lot more fun.', 100, 0), (479626, 'Scientists have to have a metaphor. All scientists start with imagination.', 567, 0), (479627, '''The Spy Who Came in from the Cold'' was the work of a wayward imagination brought to the end of its tether by political disgust and personal confusion.', 5956, 0), (479628, 'I have a visual imagination.', 140, 0), (479629, 'Of the things which nourish the imagination, humour is one of the most needful, and it is dangerous to limit or destroy it.', 22842, 0), (479630, 'My inspiration comes from so many things, it is hard to give credit to one. I find music of all kinds to be a great inspiration. A melody or a lyric can fire my imagination. Exercise is another. Endorphins fuel my thoughts - I tend to work out scenes and dialogue when I am exercising. Reading is also a great inspiration.', 6777, 0), (479631, 'No breed of cats in its proper condition can by any stretch of the imagination be thought of as even slightly ungraceful - a record against which must be pitted the depressing spectacle of impossibly flattened bulldogs, grotesquely elongated dachshunds, hideously shapeless and shaggy Airedales, and the like.', 1060, 0), (479632, 'Given free rein, our imagination can get infinite.', 2687, 0), (479633, 'Imagination decides everything.', 144, 0), (479634, 'A certificate of live birth is not the same thing by any stretch of the imagination as a birth certificate.', 64643, 0), (479635, 'I am not interested in slice of life, what I want is a slice of the imagination.', 3377, 0), (479636, 'I love audio books, and when I paint I''m always listening to a book. I find that my imagination really takes flight in the painting process when I''m listening to audio books.', 19927, 0), (479637, 'Without imagination, there can be no genuine ardor in any pursuit or for any acquisition, and without imagination, there can be no genuine morality, no profound feeling of other men''s sorrow, no ardent and persevering anxiety for their interests.', 20151, 0), (479638, 'The suicide bomber''s imagination leads him to believe in a brilliant act of heroism, when in fact he is simply blowing himself up pointlessly and taking other people''s lives.', 2065, 0), (479639, 'If you''re trying to learn how to act from a class, you''re analyzing the teachers'' movements and their intricacies, and it becomes like a pantomime of you wanting to be them, and that''s wrong. Literature is an easier way to study acting, because then you can take any kind of spin. It''s your own imagination, and your own version of it.', 66795, 0), (479640, 'There''s the tradition of the 19th-century ballets, and the 20th century has had a difficult time with that tradition. And it''s had a difficult time with many components of the Romantic imagination because of modernism.', 7842, 0), (479641, 'When you''re starting off as a young writer, you look at all the stuff that''s gone before and the stuff that''s influenced you, and you reach the ladle of your imagination into this bubbling stew pot of all of this stuff, and you pour it out. And that''s where you start from.', 14, 0), (479642, 'The Mafia exists in the American imagination because we want it to exist.', 2553, 0), (479643, 'I believe in imagination. I did Kramer vs. Kramer before I had children. But the mother I would be was already inside me.', 5983, 0), (479644, 'The great liberty of the fictional writer is to let the imagination out of the traces and see it gallop off over the horizon.', 1747, 0), (479645, 'If the history of the western moral imagination is the story of an enduring and unending revolt against human cruelty, there are few more consequential figures than Raphael Lemkin - and few whose achievements have been more ignored by the general public. It was he who coined the word ''genocide.'' He was also its victim.', 16292, 0), (479646, 'Loving a country is an act of the imagination.', 16292, 0), (479647, 'You can''t be a 21st-century science fiction writer writing about Mars without doing tips of the hat to Edgar Rice Burroughs, to Ray Bradbury, to H.G. Wells, to the guys who first put it in the public imagination that Mars was an exciting place.', 13423, 0), (479648, 'I like crafts that come out of poverty or necessity. There used to be hobby shops where you''d get your supplies, and then you''d use your imagination.', 274, 0), (479649, 'There''s this long history of colonialism and the colonial gaze when applied to matters related to China. So a lot of conceptions about China in literary representations in the West are things you can''t even fight against because they''ve been there so long that they''ve become part of the Western imagination of China.', 11096, 0), (479650, 'Growing up in a suburban home, the world seems so massive to you. It seems like cities are so big and so far away, and there''s so much in them. So your imagination runs wild, instead of when you are born in the middle of Manhattan, you''d know, like, that this is the biggest city.', 69236, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479651, 'As long as I was well fed, I was a very, very nice child. I just used my imagination and played with Barbies. I was pretty easy.', 69924, 0), (479652, 'The greatest gift you have been given is the gift of your imagination - what do you dream of wanting to do?', 16246, 0), (479653, 'A lot of these liberal churches that harbor illegal immigrants who are criminals say they are following the example of Jesus. They are following the Jesus of their imagination rather than the Jesus of the Bible.', 73508, 0), (479654, 'Obviously the facts are never just coming at you but are incorporated by an imagination that is formed by your previous experience. Memories of the past are not memories of facts but memories of your imaginings of the facts.', 398, 0), (479655, 'Writing is more about imagination than anything else. I fell in love with words. I fell in love with storytelling.', 2045, 0), (479656, 'Gender fluidity is not really feeling like you''re at one end of the spectrum or the other. For the most part, I definitely don''t identify as any gender. I''m not a guy; I don''t really feel like a woman, but obviously I was born one. So, I''m somewhere in the middle, which - in my perfect imagination - is like having the best of both sexes.', 67642, 0), (479657, 'Growing up, I had a very vivid imagination and Leonardo was like my best imaginary friend that I spoke to. When things were tough, or I was scared in an unsafe environment, I always imagined that the Ninja Turtles would come to the rescue.', 67642, 0), (479658, 'There are no shortcuts in life - only those we imagine.', 62354, 0), (479659, 'Ideas come from ordinary, everyday life. And from imagination. And from feelings. And from memories. Memories of dust in my sneakers and humming whitewalls down a hill called Monkey.', 616, 0), (479660, 'To treat your facts with imagination is one thing, to imagine your facts is another.', 1069, 0), (479661, 'A man at work, making something which he feels will exist because he is working at it and wills it, is exercising the energies of his mind and soul as well as of his body. Memory and imagination help him as he works.', 7389, 0), (479662, 'All of imagination - everything that we think, we feel, we sense - comes through the human brain. And once we create new patterns in this brain, once we shape the brain in a new way, it never returns to its original shape.', 74996, 0), (479663, 'The imagination of our children is blunted on television, and their thinking is done for them.', 74596, 0), (479664, 'It may seem unfashionable to say so, but historians should seize the imagination as well as the intellect. History is, in a sense, a story, a narrative of adventure and of vision, of character and of incident. It is also a portrait of the great general drama of the human spirit.', 8240, 0), (479665, 'When I was a young person I went to the university and I learned a rational language, to think with the left side of the brain. But in the right side of the brain you have intuition and imagination. Words are not the truth; they indicate the way to go, but you need to go alone, in silence. Symbols have a language that kills the words.', 10194, 0), (479666, 'I do think imagination is enormously valuable, and that children should be encouraged in their imagination. That''s very true.', 1716, 0), (479667, 'I suppose I''m proudest of my novels for what''s imagined in them. I think the world of my imagination is a richer and more interesting place than my personal biography.', 850, 0), (479668, 'Self-awareness is not the same thing as self-approval, any more than imagination is the same thing as day-dreaming.', 36551, 0), (479669, 'A man, to carry on a successful business, must have imagination. He must see things as in a vision, a dream of the whole thing. A man can cultivate this faculty only by an appreciation of the finer things in life.', 63087, 0), (479670, 'People are powerfully moved by imagination, belief, and knowledge. They can consider the past and future. They can make changes in their behavior out of reason in a way that animals can''t do.', 3243, 0), (479671, 'You have to really stretch your imagination to infer what the intrinsic value of Bitcoin is. I haven''t been able to do it. Maybe somebody else can.', 51811, 0), (479672, 'I don''t think that people should wear dresses two sizes too small. I just think that sexiness is better left to the imagination. It''s just more tasteful.', 71579, 0), (479673, 'Cooking with kids is not just about ingredients, recipes, and cooking. It''s about harnessing imagination, empowerment, and creativity.', 69247, 0), (479674, 'The moment a person forms a theory, his imagination sees in every object only the traits which favor that theory.', 1207, 0), (479675, 'I think that all things, in their way, reflect heavenly truth, the imagination not least.', 26, 0), (479676, 'The lunatic, the lover, and the poet, are of imagination all compact.', 13, 0), (479677, 'Sooner or later you must move down an unknown road that leads beyond the range of the imagination, and the only certainty is that the trip has to be made.', 46715, 0), (479678, 'Cowardice... is almost always simply a lack of ability to suspend functioning of the imagination.', 110, 0), (479679, 'All the works of man have their origin in creative fantasy. What right have we then to depreciate imagination.', 28934, 0), (479680, 'Don''t stay at the job for safe salary increases over time. That will never get you where you want - freedom from financial worry. Only free time, imagination, creativity, and an ability to disappear will help you deliver value that nobody ever delivered before in the history of mankind.', 20595, 0), (479681, 'I think my securities far outweigh my insecurities. I am not nearly as afraid of myself and my imagination as I used to be.', 4180, 0), (479682, 'Abstraction is one of the greatest visionary tools ever invented by human beings to imagine, decipher, and depict the world.', 19958, 0), (479683, 'Sometimes a technology is so awe-inspiring that the imagination runs away with it - often far, far away from reality. Robots are like that. A lot of big and ultimately unfulfilled promises were made in robotics early on, based on preliminary successes.', 15991, 0), (479684, 'I have a good imagination. Look, I know what it feels like to have a broken heart. I know what it feels like to feel something for somebody. I''m just too weird to be in a relationship.', 74997, 0), (479685, 'The World Series is played in my doubtless too-nostalgic imagination in some kind of autumn afternoon light, and seeing it exclusively in the bitter chill of midnight breaks the spell of even the best of games.', 7050, 0), (479686, 'I think growing up on a farm in a certain amount of isolation, with not a lot of friends nearby, makes you entertain yourself and kind of grows your imagination - being alone is quite good for all that. You make up stories, talk to the animals, let them be an audience, a bunch of cows.', 55979, 0), (479687, 'I am enough of an artist to draw freely upon my imagination.', 104, 0), (479688, 'Imagination, the supreme delight of the immortal and the immature, should be limited. In order to enjoy life, we should not enjoy it too much.', 76, 0), (479689, 'The imagination is the spur of delights... all depends upon it, it is the mainspring of everything; now, is it not by means of the imagination one knows joy? Is it not of the imagination that the sharpest pleasures arise?', 2459, 0), (479690, 'People can die of mere imagination.', 12764, 0), (479691, 'A man, to be greatly good, must imagine intensely and comprehensively; he must put himself in the place of another and of many others; the pains and pleasures of his species must become his own.', 165, 0), (479692, 'Imagine what a harmonious world it could be if every single person, both young and old shared a little of what he is good at doing.', 28763, 0), (479693, 'Life is only a dream and we are the imagination of ourselves.', 544, 0), (479694, 'I''m a dreamer with lots of energy and a vivid imagination. That''s the recipe for becoming an entertainer.', 1245, 0), (479695, 'Hypnosis is about shutting down the conscious mind and re-igniting the unconscious and the imagination, so while I give instructions to them under hypnosis, the contestants might interpret those instructions in all kinds of ways.', 70052, 0), (479696, 'Works of imagination should be written in very plain language the more purely imaginative they are the more necessary it is to be plain.', 1910, 0), (479697, 'We are the miracle of force and matter making itself over into imagination and will. Incredible. The Life Force experimenting with forms. You for one. Me for another. The Universe has shouted itself alive. We are one of the shouts.', 567, 0), (479698, 'I don''t necessarily start with the beginning of the book. I just start with the part of the story that''s most vivid in my imagination and work forward and backward from there.', 2288, 0), (479699, 'I feel like I''m a much better person when I''m developing my imagination and my innocence and my vulnerability. I like that version of me better than the version where I''m just working on my analytical mind.', 74445, 0), (479700, 'Mostly, I straddle reality and the imagination. My reality needs imagination like a bulb needs a socket. My imagination needs reality like a blind man needs a cane.', 2201, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479701, 'Living in a small town, one of the keys to survival was your imagination.', 68943, 0), (479702, 'Who cares about the men who steered your breakfast cereal through winter storms? How ironic that the more ships have grown in size and consequence, the less space they take up in our imagination.', 68042, 0), (479703, 'Men often take their imagination for their heart and they believe they are converted as soon as they think of being converted.', 144, 0), (479704, 'It would be too frightening for me to consider myself a role model. But I like the idea of not being afraid of letting your imagination rule you, to feel the freedom of expression, to let creativity be your overwhelming drive rather than other things.', 22790, 0), (479705, 'When I got large enough to go to work, while employed I was reflecting on many things that would present themselves to my imagination; and whenever an opportunity occurred of looking at a book, when the school-children were getting their lessons, I would find many things that the fertility of my own imagination had depicted to me before.', 72751, 0), (479706, 'America is a poem in our eyes; its ample geography dazzles the imagination, and it will not wait long for metres.', 760, 0), (479707, 'One can live in the shadow of an idea without grasping it.', 6481, 0), (479708, 'A man may imagine things that are false, but he can only understand things that are true, for if the things be false, the apprehension of them is not understanding.', 2482, 0), (479709, 'I still find it quite easy to find my way into a child''s imagination. We''re all Peter Pan ourselves in some respects. Everybody should keep some grip on childhood, even as a grownup.', 70741, 0), (479710, 'In your imagination, you can perfect things in a way you can''t do in your everyday life.', 74384, 0), (479711, 'You may be sure that the Americans will commit all the stupidities they can think of, plus some that are beyond imagination.', 11599, 0), (479712, 'Panic is a sudden desertion of us, and a going over to the enemy of our imagination.', 6105, 0), (479713, 'Aptitude found in the understanding and is often inherited. Genius coming from reason and imagination, rarely.', 267, 0), (479714, 'There are many ways to be free. One of them is to transcend reality by imagination, as I try to do.', 23, 0), (479715, 'One longs for a director with a sense of imagination.', 11118, 0), (479716, 'The openness of rural Nebraska certainly influenced me. That openness, in a way, fosters the imagination. But growing up, Lincoln wasn''t a small town. It was a college town. It had record stores and was a liberal place.', 74461, 0), (479717, 'It would be a bitter cosmic joke if we destroy ourselves due to atrophy of the imagination.', 193, 0), (479718, 'I used my imagination to make the grass whatever color I wanted it to be.', 1459, 0), (479719, 'The woman who appeals to a man''s vanity may stimulate him, the woman who appeals to his heart may attract him, but it is the woman who appeals to his imagination who gets him.', 2362, 0), (479720, 'When something is such a creative medium as the web, the limits to it are our imagination.', 59325, 0), (479721, 'What''s in front of you is a whole world of experiences beyond your imagination. Put yourself, and your growth and development, first.', 71159, 0), (479722, 'I''m always easily frightened and I hate being scared. I''ve never been able to go on the haunted house rides at carnivals of anything like that my imagination just takes over! ', 69400, 0), (479723, 'In a rehearsal room, your real resource as an actor aren''t the things around you; your resources are your imagination and your director and the other actors. In those close quarters, your imagination and your skills are what you turn to.', 74998, 0), (479724, 'The one thing emphasized in any creative writing course is ''write what you know,'' and that automatically drives a wooden stake through the heart of imagination. If they really understood the mysterious process of creating fiction, they would say, ''You can write about anything you can imagine.''', 105, 0), (479725, 'I''m attracted to stories that excite my imagination, stories that, as I''m reading the script, I feel it, I can see it, I can hear the characters. I''m attracted to characters that are real, that tap into something inside me that I haven''t explored yet.', 73173, 0), (479726, 'To create a new standard, it takes something that''s not just a little bit different; it takes something that''s really new and really captures people''s imagination, and the Macintosh, of all the machines I''ve ever seen, is the only one that meets that standard.', 1133, 0), (479727, 'If you were a successful upper-middle-class Negro girl in the 1950s and ''60s, you were, in practice and imagination, a white Protestant upper middle-class girl. Young, good-looking white women were the most desirable creatures in the world. It was hard not to want to imitate them; it was highly toxic, too, as we would learn.', 68863, 0), (479728, 'I was always extremely creative. I was very artistic and never strong with numbers or science. I wanted to be an artist or a fashion designer. I wanted to be something that allowed for a lot of imagination.', 68878, 0), (479729, 'My country has contrived for me the most insignificant office that ever the invention of man contrived or his imagination conceived.', 4179, 0), (479730, 'The face of nature and civilization in this our country is to a certain point a very sufficient literary field. But it will yield its secrets only to a really grasping imagination. To write well and worthily of American things one need even more than elsewhere to be a master.', 561, 0), (479731, 'The source and center of all man''s creative power... is his power of making images, or the power of imagination.', 10101, 0), (479732, 'The innovative process is a fragile one, dependent on a complex, often messy interplay of imagination, competition, and exchange. Curbing new ideas hurts not only individual creators but the audience for which they create and the posterity that inherits their legacy.', 68175, 0), (479733, 'Without imagination we can go nowhere. And imagination is not restricted to the arts. Every scientist I have met who has been a success has had to imagine.', 9002, 0), (479734, 'I think life is about having the mixture of the curiosity of an older person and the imagination of a child.', 57419, 0), (479735, 'Woman is the sun, an extraordinary creature, one that makes the imagination gallop.', 74999, 0), (479736, 'One travels to run away from routine, that dreadful routine that kills all imagination and all our capacity for enthusiasm.', 70829, 0), (479737, 'Vulgarity begins when imagination succumbs to the explicit.', 18677, 0), (479738, 'I have always felt that the truth is prophetic, and that if you describe precisely what you see and give it life with your imagination, then what you write ought to have lasting value, no matter what the mood of your prose.', 1979, 0), (479739, 'Some stories are true that never happened.', 10, 0), (479740, 'Personally, I would sooner have written Alice in Wonderland than the whole Encyclopedia Britannica.', 9981, 0), (479741, 'The human mind evolved always in the company of the human body, and of the animal body before it was human. The intricate connections of mind and body must exceed our imagination, as from our point of view we are peculiarly prevented from observing them.', 69973, 0), (479742, 'I''ve spent my life butting my head against other people''s lack of imagination.', 2317, 0), (479743, 'Here is everything which can lay hold of the eye, ear and imagination - everything which can charm and bewitch the simple and ignorant. I wonder how Luther ever broke the spell.', 4179, 0), (479744, 'You will recognize your own path when you come upon it, because you will suddenly have all the energy and imagination you will ever need.', 74995, 0), (479745, 'One of the virtues of being very young is that you don''t let the facts get in the way of your imagination.', 1260, 0), (479746, 'Poetry is that art which selects and arranges the symbols of thought in such a manner as to excite the imagination the most powerfully and delightfully.', 70801, 0), (479747, 'You expect far too much of a first sentence. Think of it as analogous to a good country breakfast: what we want is something simple, but nourishing to the imagination.', 14106, 0), (479748, 'My main point here is that if you are the child of God and God is a part of you, the in your imagination God suppose to look like you. And when you accept a picture of the deity assigned to you by another people, you become the spiritual prisoners of that other people.', 50699, 0), (479749, 'To put down an ideogram of a table so that people will recognize it as a table is not the work of a painter, but to sense it for a moment as a magic carpet with a leg hanging down at each corner is the beginning of a painter''s imagination.', 75000, 0), (479750, 'Dr. Einstein was not successful in school, but he found something in the air from his own imagination and his own brain power, and look what he did.', 821, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479751, 'I always believe it''s better to have 30 imaginations working on a project, rather than one imagination telling the other 29 what to do.', 71114, 0), (479752, 'Writing gives me the opportunity to explore ideas, play with language, solve problems, use my imagination, and draw on my own childhood.', 8654, 0), (479753, 'I loved the world of imagination.', 1486, 0), (479754, 'Sometimes I feel like a figment of my own imagination.', 1059, 0), (479755, 'Imagination... its limits are only those of the mind itself.', 14284, 0), (479756, 'He is the true enchanter, whose spell operates, not upon the senses, but upon the imagination and the heart.', 944, 0), (479757, 'The world is not run by thought, nor by imagination, but by opinion.', 37014, 0), (479758, 'Writing poetry is the hard manual labor of the imagination.', 9514, 0), (479759, 'But I''m never gonna get to a point in my life where what it costs to shoot a movie is going to determine what it is. The limits of my imagination is the only thing that''s gonna stop me.', 75001, 0), (479760, 'I''ve always felt that what I have going for me is not my imagination, because everyone has an imagination. What I have is a relentlessly controlled imagination. What looks like wild invention is actually quite carefully calculated.', 195, 0), (479761, 'I was raised not to be afraid to show emotion or imagination.', 4141, 0), (479762, 'Many memory techniques involve creating unforgettable imagery, in your mind''s eye. That''s an act of imagination. Creating really weird imagery really quickly was the most fun part of my training to compete in the U.S. Memory Competition.', 13388, 0), (479763, 'With me, writing is 60% imagination, 30% people you know and 10% you don''t know where it comes from.', 74763, 0), (479764, 'I grew up believing my sister was from the planet Neptune and had been sent down to Earth to kill me. I believed this because my sister Emily convinced me of it when I was a toddler. I think she''d seen Invasion of the Body Snatchers and her imagination ran away with her. There''s a part of me that still believes it.', 22856, 0), (479765, 'Students are rewarded for memorization, not imagination or resourcefulness.', 50266, 0), (479766, 'Games are the way we keep romance alive. They''re based in human hardwiring. Playing hard-to-get or leaving a little to the imagination allows the woman to be wooed and appreciated and the man to be challenged and intrigued.', 52746, 0), (479767, 'It is literature which for me opened the mysterious and decisive doors of imagination and understanding. To see the way others see. To think the way others think. And above all, to feel.', 2065, 0), (479768, 'Nature''s imagination is so boundless compared to our own meager human imagination.', 3628, 0), (479769, 'Your heart will be shattered by sorrow if you force it to live in tomorrow''s ephemeral imagination - world instead of in today''s eternal reality - now.', 4786, 0), (479770, 'I always have this imagination, something I want to use. I don''t understand the idea of leisure time.', 75002, 0), (479771, 'Some music comes from a real place; some music comes from your imagination. It''s difficult to find out what''s real and what''s not, especially with the gangster stuff.', 11834, 0), (479772, 'I''ve got an overactive brain. I enjoy work, I enjoy life, and I''m not good at relaxing. I''ve also never slept very much due to this overactive imagination and my brain constantly thinking.', 73217, 0), (479773, 'Taking a comic strip character is very hard to write. Because comics are meant to work in one page, to work in frames with minimalistic dialogue. And a lot of it is left to the imagination of the reader. To do that in film, you''ve got to be a little more explanatory. And that requires a good screenplay and good dialogue.', 68428, 0), (479774, 'The fictive structure, my work, my imagination, my books are about the details, the huge construction about culture, Islamic culture or modern Turkey. They''re all intertwined.', 128, 0), (479775, 'People seem to have trouble with the imagination. They can''t believe that you can just pull things out of your brain like that.', 227, 0), (479776, 'Using my imagination and creativity is exciting to me.', 73239, 0), (479777, 'I sometimes think that so much of our life takes place inside our heads - in memory or imagination or interpretation or speculation - that if I really want to change my life, I might best begin by changing my mind.', 711, 0), (479778, 'Bad people are, from the point of view of art, fascinating studies. They represent colour, variety and strangeness. Good people exasperate one''s reason; bad people stir one''s imagination.', 40, 0), (479779, 'I get ideas from my own personal experiences, from my imagination, and from my research and from old stories.', 49445, 0), (479780, 'Remember that your imagination is yours and yours alone. You have the inborn capacity to use it in any way that you choose. No one else is responsible for your imagination. Anything placed in your imagination and held there ultimately becomes your reality.', 21729, 0), (479781, 'Although technology has enhanced our lives in many ways, it has also ensured the erosion of imagination.', 467, 0), (479782, 'I get irritated with the world. I get irritated with politicians. I get very irritated with governments and with corporations, but in terms of imagination - my imagination is always fertile. I''m either thinking of my own things or constantly engaged by the things that other people do.', 1883, 0), (479783, 'Walt Disney had a nuclear imagination before the advent of nuclear, some comprehension of apocalypse and rapture deep in his genes.', 8777, 0), (479784, 'The appeal of the spectrally macabre is generally narrow because it demands from the reader a certain degree of imagination and a capacity for detachment from everyday life.', 1060, 0), (479785, 'I think acting is a work of imagination.', 69234, 0), (479786, 'The writer''s goal is to try to make it frightening without describing it too much, and yet not making it so grey that you don''t know what''s going on... Your imagination can imagine all sorts of really horrible things, and if you''re able to prolong that feeling, then you''ve succeeded.', 49754, 0), (479787, 'I always struggle with making the technical aspects of the plot fit with the story that''s unfolding in my imagination.', 72200, 0), (479788, 'People are always saying it''s the end of the Gutenberg era. More to the point, it''s a return to an oral era. The Gutenberg galaxy was about the written word. At its best, the digital era is part of the rediscovery of the oral. At its worst, it''s a Kafkaesque victory of the bureaucratic over the imagination.', 30260, 0), (479789, 'Children depend mightily on animals for comfort, inspiration, imagination, and art. And parents have long recognized this.', 4572, 0), (479790, 'The public has an appetite for anything about imagination - anything that is as far away from reality as is creatively possible.', 5194, 0), (479791, 'What really fascinates me is this need that is so strong now that if you read a work of the imagination you instantly have to say, ''Oh, what this really is is so-and-so,'' reducing it to a simple formula.', 217, 0), (479792, 'Teachers need to feel they are trusted. They must be allowed some leeway to use their imagination; otherwise, teaching loses all sense of wonder and excitement.', 1330, 0), (479793, '''Harry Potter'' really harnessed the imagination of so many young-adult minds, and it''s the same with the ''Divergent'' series.', 22748, 0), (479794, 'The imagination imitates. It is the critical spirit that creates.', 40, 0), (479795, 'You have to come in and be that character when you walk into the room. That''s what one of my first acting teachers taught me. You know, don''t go in there being Jennifer and then expect to flip and change, because they''re not going to have that imagination.', 24514, 0), (479796, 'Death? Why this fuss about death? Use your imagination, try to visualize a world without death! Death is the essential condition of life, not an evil.', 7807, 0), (479797, 'Today the function of the artist is to bring imagination to science and science to imagination, where they meet, in the myth.', 9518, 0), (479798, 'If we find it hard to believe that winning millions might not be so lucky after all, we just don''t have a good enough imagination. If I fantasise about winning the lottery, it doesn''t take long before all sorts of worrisome potential consequences occur to me.', 67531, 0), (479799, 'My hope is that this life is not all there is. This life is like preparation for what is coming next, and what is coming next is something so glorious that the Bible says minds can''t conceive it, eye has never seen, your imagination could never even enter into all that God is preparing for those who love him.', 9414, 0), (479800, 'I just have a relationship with my imagination. It''s like my friend, almost.', 922, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479801, 'I don''t feel there''s any reason to apologise for having a wicked imagination. I think it''s important as a maker of fantasy and of horror.', 107, 0), (479802, 'With its imagination and large sales, Apple has become the world''s most valuable IT company. However people are starting to have doubts regarding Apple''s silence on heavy metal pollution problems.', 75003, 0), (479803, 'Never, and I mean never, allow anyone else''s ideas of who you can or can''t become sully your dream or pollute your imagination. This is your territory, and a ''Keep Out'' sign is a great thing to erect at all entrances to your imagination.', 21729, 0), (479804, 'I don''t believe my house was haunted. I think I had an overactive imagination, and I was so convinced that those around me became convinced, too.', 62003, 0), (479805, 'Without this playing with fantasy no creative work has ever yet come to birth. The debt we owe to the play of the imagination is incalculable.', 28934, 0), (479806, 'I had an incredibly full life with my imagination: I used to have all sorts of trolls and things; I had a wonderful world around my toys and invented people. I don''t mean I had imaginary friends; I just had this big imagination thing going on. I didn''t need any imaginary friends, because I had so much other stuff going on.', 69934, 0), (479807, 'I feel like my imagination was crafted by Tolkien. He seemed to tap into that childhood intrigue of secret doors and hidden worlds.', 69193, 0), (479808, 'In many a piece of music, it''s the pause or the rest that gives the piece its beauty and its shape. And I know I, as a writer, will often try to include a lot of empty space on the page so that the reader can complete my thoughts and sentences and so that her imagination has room to breathe.', 711, 0), (479809, 'I didn''t like Barbie dolls, so I used to have this overactive imagination, and I used to pretend to be all these different things. My weird childhood fetishes seem to have come to life now as an actor.', 66931, 0), (479810, 'People write memoirs because they lack the imagination to make things up.', 105, 0), (479811, 'In my wildest imagination, I never thought that the fifth of six children born to Helen and Buddy Watts - in a poor black neighborhood, in the poor rural community of Eufaula, Oklahoma - would someday be called Congressman.', 67449, 0), (479812, 'Nonfiction is both easier and harder to write than fiction. It''s easier because the facts are already laid out before you, and there is already a narrative arc. What makes it harder is that you are not free to use your imagination and creativity to fill in any missing gaps within the story.', 870, 0), (479813, 'The novel and the film of ''The Color Purple'' are both works of the imagination that make claim to historical truth.', 23303, 0), (479814, 'It''s through the small things that we develop our moral imagination, so that we can understand the sufferings of others.', 1621, 0), (479815, 'We especially need imagination in science.', 6136, 0), (479816, 'I probably became an actor because of my vivid imagination, and doing voice-over really sort of takes me back to that.', 70285, 0), (479817, 'It is usually the imagination that is wounded first, rather than the heart; it being much more sensitive.', 1049, 0), (479818, 'I feel very lucky to make a living from my imagination I''m very grateful for that. I like that what I do is create. I''m feeling very lucky to have had the career I had. It''s gone much longer and bigger than I ever thought it would be.', 922, 0), (479819, 'People may think I''m trying something new by telling stories, but they''re just jokes connected to give the illusion of stories. But really, I just continue using my imagination and creating. That''s what I do.', 922, 0), (479820, 'When I started the Imagination Library in my hometown, I never dreamed that one day we would be helping Scottish kids.', 1300, 0), (479821, 'What distinguishes a great artist from a weak one is first their sensibility and tenderness; second, their imagination, and third, their industry.', 2065, 0), (479822, 'Reading has been the fuel of my motivation: it has changed the direction in which I have traveled, and it has enhanced my creative imagination more than any other activity I have ever pursued.', 1692, 0), (479823, 'Few people have the imagination for reality.', 282, 0), (479824, 'Were it not for imagination a man would be as happy in arms of a chambermaid as of a duchess.', 2087, 0), (479825, 'One is never fortunate or as unfortunate as one imagines.', 154, 0), (479826, 'Experience teaches that when the will and imagination are in conflict, the imagination usually wins. What we imagine may defeat our reason and make us slaves to what we taste, see, hear, smell, and feel in the mind''s eye. The body is indeed the servant of the mind.', 4294, 0), (479827, 'The human race is governed by its imagination.', 1702, 0), (479828, 'I''ve done a lot of bad things. Use your imagination.', 746, 0), (479829, 'Taste refers to the past, imagination to the future.', 12469, 0), (479830, 'Imagination has rules, but we can only guess what they are.', 12469, 0), (479831, 'Ray Bradbury is one who is contributing to the understanding of the imagination and the curiosity of the human race.', 25693, 0), (479832, 'I can''t satisfy myself with just trying to tie all of my imagination into music, especially when music is not appreciated as an art form as much as it used to be.', 2519, 0), (479833, 'Mars has long exerted a pull on the human imagination. The erratically moving red star in the sky was seen as sinister or violent by the ancients: The Greeks identified it with Ares, the god of war; the Babylonians named it after Nergal, god of the underworld. To the ancient Chinese, it was Ying-huo, the fire planet.', 135, 0), (479834, 'Whoever has once been truly unsettled by a work of the imagination will never give loyalty to a single idea, belief system, religious faith or party.', 4223, 0), (479835, 'Not everyone is fortunate enough to earn their living playing. But what draws people to art and artists is a desire to enjoy the propinquity of play. For it is the very freedom of the imagination. And what else were we born to do, but imagine freely?', 4223, 0), (479836, 'While the sciences are hugely important, let us not leave behind a child''s imagination.', 60302, 0), (479837, 'I always felt that what is scary is actually hearing someone tell you what they think they see. That sense of invisibility makes things a lot scarier, since your imagination tends to fill in the gaps.', 69246, 0), (479838, 'We can conceive of eternity because we cannot conceive of a cessation of time. We can conceive of infinite space because we cannot conceive of so much matter that our imagination will not stand upon the farthest star and see infinite space beyond.', 67335, 0), (479839, 'My problem is that my imagination won''t turn off. I wake up so excited I can''t eat breakfast. I''ve never run out of energy. It''s not like OPEC oil I don''t worry about a premium going on my energy. It''s just always been there. I got it from my mom. ', 5194, 0), (479840, 'We are all innovators, we all like to use our imagination, which is our greatest tool.', 10615, 0), (479841, 'Our thoughts and imagination are the only real limits to our possibilities.', 4025, 0), (479842, 'Believing you''re something that you''re not excites the mind and the imagination. And it''s hopeful.', 68239, 0), (479843, 'I''ve always had a slightly overactive imagination.', 1593, 0), (479844, 'Many scientists think that philosophy has no place, so for me it''s a sad time because the role of reflection, contemplation, meditation, self inquiry, insight, intuition, imagination, creativity, free will, is in a way not given any importance, which is the domain of philosophers.', 1194, 0), (479845, 'We''re living in a time when the world has suddenly discovered India because it''s run out of raw material for its imagination. The raw materials for imagination are inexhaustible here.', 1194, 0), (479846, 'Being on a trapeze is like dreaming. I feel totally outside of myself when I''m flying. You know, designing shoes, my imagination is flying in my drawings.', 18155, 0), (479847, 'I always appreciated the magnitude of my mother''s imagination. She always saw beauty in what was broken, and she''d preserve it.', 38496, 0), (479848, 'I know there''s been a lot that''s been said about animated voice work, as though it''s ''you can do this in your jeans and there''s no camera and no pressure there. It''s no big deal. It''s easy.'' The truth is, it''s really a great test: how deep is your ability is to access your imagination?', 67437, 0), (479849, 'Science fiction is a way that I can go into the abstract, go into the imagination, and audiences are still willing to go along for the ride.', 67437, 0), (479850, 'Often you hear stories about never working with children. I disagree because children still have that residual magical thinking. They haven''t had their imagination knocked out of them by turning into adults and life experiences.', 67437, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479851, 'I tend to like to read history - recent history, because I find that much more intriguing than just a writer''s imagination.', 16709, 0), (479852, 'Doubt is the father of invention.', 224, 0), (479853, 'Liberty: One of Imagination''s most precious possessions.', 224, 0), (479854, 'I use so much of myself in everything I do. I think every actor does because you have no one else to go to but yourself and your own imagination.', 67399, 0), (479855, 'Free enterprise empowers entrepreneurs who have ideas and imagination, investors who take risks, and workers who hone their skills and offer their labor.', 66572, 0), (479856, 'Imagination is a poor matter when it has to part company with understanding.', 3061, 0), (479857, 'Imagination is a pretty powerful thing, and when you''re in the moment and you''re riding a train and you''re asked to look scared, I don''t know, it just kind of works out. And in those moments where you''re actually doing some of the stunts, then it''s not so hard at all, because there''s an actual fear there.', 12497, 0), (479858, 'I came from a childhood where I spent a lot of time alone and a lot of time just living with my imagination, and a certain amount of the adult world was kind of alienating.', 49828, 0), (479859, 'There''s a particular sensitivity required to be an artist, and a certain vulnerability, perhaps, and also, somewhere between, you''re in your body a lot, too. It''s much more physical than one would imagine because I think it''s the body where the imagination lives somehow. I do feel the imagination isn''t just in the brain up there.', 10407, 0), (479860, 'I love theatrics and have a huge imagination: Why would I want to sit onstage and sing a bunch of ballads back-to-back?', 11155, 0), (479861, 'No film has captivated my imagination more than ''King Kong.'' I''m making movies today because I saw this film when I was 9 years old.', 3497, 0), (479862, '''The Lord of the Rings,'' published in the mid-1950s, was intended as a prehistory to our own world. It was perceived by Tolkien to be a small but significant episode in a vast alternate mythology constructed entirely out of his own imagination.', 3497, 0), (479863, 'Because of my faith and my imagination, I was able to enjoy my childhood, even though it was tough.', 67006, 0), (479864, 'I have a huge, active imagination, and I think I''m really scared of being alone; because if I''m left to my own devices, I''ll just turn into a madwoman.', 70251, 0), (479865, 'I''ve always had a really active imagination. Lots of kids have imaginary friends. Mine just took on a rather demonic form.', 70251, 0), (479866, 'There is a boundary to men''s passions when they act from feelings but none when they are under the influence of imagination.', 2026, 0), (479867, 'But if I have a lot of imagination, I could tell myself whatever I wanted, you know. I handle myself quite well. I''m kind of fascist with myself, you know. There''s no discussion. There is an order. You follow it.', 306, 0), (479868, 'I do a lot of curiosity buying; I buy it if I like the album cover, I buy it if I like the name of the band, anything that sparks my imagination.', 2251, 0), (479869, 'I suspect that even most conservatives would prefer to live in the kind of world conjured up in the liberals'' imagination rather than in the kind of world we are in fact stuck with.', 2589, 0), (479870, 'Obviously the imagination is fueled by emotions beyond the control of the conscious mind.', 852, 0), (479871, 'There can be no passion, and by consequence no love, where there is not imagination.', 20151, 0), (479872, 'There must be room for the imagination to exercise its powers we must conceive and apprehend a thousand things which we do not actually witness.', 20151, 0), (479873, 'There is nothing that human imagination can figure brilliant and enviable that human genius and skill do not aspire to realize.', 20151, 0), (479874, 'I''d stand on the side of the road when I was just a little girl singing on trash cans. People would roll down their windows saying, ''Isn''t she cute''. I had a vivid imagination. I always pretended it was some big stage.', 69257, 0), (479875, 'My imagination is so far out there already. People couldn''t imagine what goes on in my brain.', 69257, 0), (479876, 'The theater itself is a lie. Its deaths are mere special effects. Its tales never happened. Even the histories are distorted for dramatic effect. The theater is unnatural, a place of imagination. But the theater tells the audience something true: that the world requires judgments.', 68175, 0), (479877, '''A Princess of Mars'' may not have exerted the same colossal pull that Tarzan had on the global imagination, but its influence on generations of readers cannot be underestimated.', 560, 0), (479878, 'Speculators get a bad rap. In the popular imagination they''re greedy, heedless, and amoral, adept at price manipulations and dirty tricks. In reality, they often play a key role in making markets run smoothly.', 11156, 0), (479879, 'There''s basically an element of fiction in everything you remember. Imagination and memory are almost the same brain processes. When I write fiction, I know that I''m using a bunch of lies that I''ve made up to create some form of truth. When I write a memoir, I''m using true elements to create something that will always be somehow fictionalized.', 441, 0), (479880, 'A nickname is the heaviest stone that the devil can throw at a man. It is a bugbear to the imagination, and, though we do not believe in it, it still haunts our apprehensions.', 8948, 0), (479881, 'The degree in which a poet''s imagination dominates reality is, in the end, the exact measure of his importance and dignity.', 2683, 0), (479882, 'My proudest moment was probably when my oldest boy finished law school and went on to become an FBI agent. It was just beyond my imagination that - with my background - my own son would become an FBI agent.', 68352, 0), (479883, 'I''ve proven I''m courageous. I''m gutsier than anybody; I''ve got a better imagination than anybody; I''m essentially more creative than any other actor I know, and I''ve proven I take risks. I don''t think I need to prove anything to myself any more.', 68375, 0), (479884, 'To make extra money, my parents would sell eggs and chickens. I was very little. I remember a chicken''s head being chopped off with the chicken running around. I wasn''t sure if my imagination was running away with me or if it really happened. It really happened.', 68375, 0), (479885, 'Anything I did with the WWE was not therapeutic by any stretch of the imagination. The reality is that nobody''s going to tell you that, because they have an umbilical cord hooked to Vince McMahon. I, ladies and gentlemen, do not.', 67851, 0), (479886, 'The new age of terrorism isn''t on the battlefield: it''s in your own backyard. Whether it''s at a concert in France or a restaurant in the United States, terrorism doesn''t have to happen in a military installation by any stretch of the imagination.', 67851, 0), (479887, 'Whether it''s at a concert in France or a restaurant in the United States, terrorism doesn''t have to happen in a military installation by any stretch of the imagination.', 67851, 0), (479888, 'I didn''t choose Goldberg because I wanted to be the flagship for the Jewish movement, not by any stretch of the imagination. I chose Goldberg because no one else can own it.', 67851, 0), (479889, 'It''s what still excites me most about acting: letting your imagination go places it''s never been before. There''s nothing better than that.', 70666, 0), (479890, 'Out with stereotypes, feminism proclaims. But stereotypes are the west''s stunning sexual personae, the vehicles of art''s assault against nature. The moment there is imagination, there is myth.', 1920, 0), (479891, 'Ideas seem to come from everywhere - my life, everything I see, hear, and read, and most of all, from my imagination. I have a lot of imagination.', 1041, 0), (479892, 'For some reason I can''t explain, artist and musicians tend to look younger than our age. Being in music, you need this youthful sense of discovery and wonder for what you''re doing and keep your imagination open. That''s a youthful way of looking at life and I think that reflects in how you age.', 67485, 0), (479893, 'Edgy is fine - I''m not a prude by any stretch of the imagination - but what''s wrong with a good ol'' belly laugh? I miss that.', 51091, 0), (479894, 'I want to liberate my imagination and my mind with every kind of movie. That is what I wanted to do all my life.', 10194, 0), (479895, 'So often, science fiction helps to get young people interested in science. That''s why I don''t mind talking about science fiction. It has a real role to play: to seize the imagination.', 1821, 0), (479896, 'I don''t want to go on much longer, really. I think that would suggest a lack of imagination. A certain lack of dignity also.', 1259, 0), (479897, 'Nobody would know it to look at me, but the movies I liked as a kid were musicals - ''All That Jazz,'' ''Hair,'' ''Fame,'' ''Annie,'' all that stuff - that''s where my little youthful imagination was.', 25658, 0), (479898, 'I have more of a vivid imagination than I have talent. I cook up ideas. It''s just a characteristic.', 28610, 0), (479899, 'It takes no imagination to live within your means.', 28610, 0), (479900, 'I''m essentially the result of other people''s imagination. And that''s fine. Because of other people''s imagination, I''ve played parts I would never have thought I could do. Still, I''ve never had a hankering or an ambition for any particular role.', 67836, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479901, 'Acting is an imaginative exercise. It would be odd if you didn''t try to identify with the roles you play, but I think I can differentiate between where my imagination is leading me and where I actually am.', 67836, 0), (479902, 'I would love to meet J.K. Rowling and tell her how much I admire her writing and am amazed by her imagination. I read every ''Harry Potter'' book as it came out and looked forward to each new one. I am rereading them now with my kids and enjoying them every bit as much. She made me look at jelly beans in a whole new way.', 1770, 0), (479903, 'The Anthroposophical Society is different from other societies in that it will not tolerate any figments of the imagination in its organization but is constructed on the basis of reality.', 14254, 0), (479904, 'Sometimes when you''ve got too much money you lose your imagination.', 69336, 0), (479905, 'The realities of the world seldom measure up to the sublime designs of human imagination.', 24882, 0), (479906, 'A good comic explores the imagination, but it''s always got to have those notes of truth running through it.', 68251, 0), (479907, 'I wouldn''t say I have comedy chops. I guess you get lucky with good writing because I don''t think I''m a comedian by any stretch of the imagination.', 68251, 0), (479908, 'For me, when I do my best acting, it''s mainly imagination. Then I really have a lot of fun with it.', 68251, 0), (479909, 'Life is possible only by the deficiencies of our imagination and memory.', 70201, 0), (479910, 'Everything, I think, about acting is based on imagination.', 69337, 0), (479911, 'The faking of feelings is a sin against the imagination.', 1422, 0), (479912, 'I''m very conscious that people dear to me are alive in my imagination - poets in particular.', 1422, 0), (479913, 'I''m not such a fan of imagination. If you''re alive to details, they oftentimes suggest a richer or deeper imaginative line than you would have imagined.', 9683, 0), (479914, 'I''ve developed a theory that there''s an inverse relationship between money and imagination. That if you''ve got lots of imagination then you don''t really need much money, and if you''ve got lots of money then you won''t bother with much imagination.', 1001, 0), (479915, 'Well, I''m not a method actress by any stretch of the imagination so the best thing that I can do is be as real as possible and find whatever commonality in that character that I can see myself.', 18940, 0), (479916, 'Reading a book, watching a movie, going to a play, it''s transporting, and very, very exciting. And to be a part of that, creating things with your imagination, whoa.', 47094, 0), (479917, 'Another side to me is this very sexual being. When I look back on my life, it''s always been there. It''s been there since I was 10 years old, having the imagination that I had.', 47095, 0), (479918, 'I had a pretty sexual imagination for a kid.', 47095, 0), (479919, 'Don Quixote''s misfortune is not his imagination, but Sancho Panza.', 629, 0), (479920, 'For those without money, the road to that treasure house of the imagination begins at the public library.', 2553, 0), (479921, 'I don''t profess to be Shonda Rhimes by any stretch of the imagination, or Dick Wolf. They''re icons. I''m a filmmaker.', 68259, 0), (479922, 'I wanted to inspire every little girl who wants to be a dancer to fire their imagination about the joys of being on the stage.', 68905, 0), (479923, 'I want everyone to put their views forward, every union branch, every party branch, so we develop organically the strengths we all have, the imagination we all have.', 50602, 0), (479924, 'The longer I look at something, the more my imagination churns and I can find somewhere to put it.', 67026, 0), (479925, 'What I really have in my head, my imagination, my understanding of music, I never really get that out.', 22730, 0), (479926, 'When television captured the popular imagination of the 1950s, a rash of movies satirized Hollywood while also mythologizing it.', 8777, 0), (479927, 'The arts stimulate imagination. They provoke thought. And then, having done that, all sorts of other things happen.', 67032, 0), (479928, 'As an actor, whether I''m playing Othello on stage or David Estes on ''Homeland,'' that ability to give into your imagination is something that I enjoy.', 70638, 0), (479929, 'Most of my interests in terms of writing are dark, so it''s discordant how much I try to lock into the vibe of wherever I''m at. Inhabiting the life of the imagination is the nature of survival strategy - you build yourself little worlds to enjoy.', 16432, 0), (479930, 'I tend to be really spacey, but I don''t think it''s because I''m unintelligent - it''s just my imagination and a little bit of ADD.', 66993, 0), (479931, 'My imagination ran 24/7, and to me, every problem was a challenge to solve and new product to create. It wasn''t until I started teaching that I realized that not everyone''s head worked the same way.', 68928, 0), (479932, 'As one of four daughters, I grew up with an imaginary brother - wondering what it would have been like if one of us had been a boy. There''s no question that there was a phantom boy child in my imagination when I was young.', 2777, 0), (479933, 'I don''t want to discredit people''s individuality, but I think people are pretty much the same. People are very similar. If you have a good enough imagination then you can feel things that you personally have never done before. That''s acting.', 55840, 0), (479934, 'Los Angeles gives one the feeling of the future more strongly than any city I know of. A bad future, too, like something out of Fritz Lang''s feeble imagination.', 497, 0), (479935, 'You know what''s better than building things up in your imagination? Building things up in real life.', 14605, 0), (479936, 'A lot of things that I write about have happened to people around me, if not necessarily to me or in the organizations I''ve worked in. Having said that, it''s fiction and has a lot to do with my imagination and creativity.', 69903, 0), (479937, 'When James Bond presses the watch and the car explodes, the writer doesn''t go into the science of it. One should leave it to the leap of faith. I have tried to explain as much as possible, and what I can''t, I have left it to people''s imagination.', 69903, 0), (479938, 'You can''t make money without selling something real. You can''t make something real without first imagination manifesting itself in your head. You can''t have imagination without surrendering yourself to an idea that you want to create something of value to other human beings.', 20595, 0), (479939, 'Businessmen are not in business to lose customers, and schools do not exist to free their clients from the agencies of mass persuasion. School and media possess a productive monopoly upon the imagination of a child.', 11500, 0), (479940, 'Imagination grows by exercise, and contrary to common belief, is more powerful in the mature than in the young.', 235, 0), (479941, 'You know when you''re a child and your imagination is limitless and you really believe in magic? I thought I had super powers.', 66719, 0), (479942, 'My production style is all about imagination. I want my audience to use their imagination when they watch my videos. My goal is for my voice to be that little hope of encouragement in your head when you walk out your door.', 66719, 0), (479943, 'Many hedge fund managers have become billionaires perhaps this - plus their reputations as the smartest guys in the room - is why they have captured the investing public''s imagination.', 68893, 0), (479944, 'I had this desire to see the world. I couldn''t see any of it, but I saw it in my imagination, and that''s why I always read books, and I could go to Mars or Middle Earth or the Hyborian age.', 169, 0), (479945, 'To bolster his right flank and attract women voters, John McCain had cynically opted for a running mate who was, by any stretch of the imagination, unqualified for a position a heartbeat away from the presidency.', 50301, 0), (479946, 'It''s an imaginative thing we do; it''s about immersing oneself in one''s imagination. If you''re a novelist, you do it with pen and paper. We do it with our bodies.', 70670, 0), (479947, 'I''m a big fan of imagination. I think it''s the strongest tool we have, and there are some things that you just can''t practice.', 70670, 0), (479948, 'I would love to do a western. I would love to play an explorer. That is always something that has really captured my imagination since I was a kid, like James Cook or Magellan or Earnest Shackleton.', 70258, 0), (479949, 'I think that being read to every night is the reason why I was plowing through volume after volume of ''Nancy Drew'' books all by myself by the time I reached the first grade. I loved stories. I loved the escape. I had a vivid imagination.', 69076, 0), (479950, 'The Jewish festival of freedom is the oldest continuously observed religious ritual in the world. Across the centuries, Passover has never lost its power to inspire the imagination of successive generations of Jews with its annually re-enacted drama of slavery and liberation.', 4059, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (479951, 'In Ronald Reagan''s chaotic childhood, the imagination was armor. There is nothing unusual about that; transcending the doubts, hesitations, and fears swirling around you by casting yourself internally as the hero of your own adventure story is a characteristic psychic defense mechanism of the Boy Who Disappears.', 11762, 0), (479952, 'Companies like Google and Facebook may offer jobs allowing or requiring imagination and creativity, but the whole of Silicon Valley accounts for only 3 percent of national income and a smaller percentage of national employment.', 69921, 0), (479953, 'The map we made of the 3,000-year-old city of Tanis requires no imagination. It has buildings, streets, admin complexes, houses - clear as day.', 69935, 0), (479954, 'A-POC unleashes the freedom of imagination. It''s for people who are curious, who have inner energy - the energy of life and living.', 67846, 0), (479955, 'I would find myself laughing and wondering where these ideas came from. You can call it imagination, I suppose. But I was grateful for wherever they came from.', 1039, 0), (479956, 'Everything that is new or uncommon raises a pleasure in the imagination, because it fills the soul with an agreeable surprise, gratifies its curiosity, and gives it an idea of which it was not before possessed.', 2868, 0), (479957, 'I know how fiction matters to me, because if I want to express myself, I have to make up a story. Some people call it imagination. To me, it''s not imagination. It''s just a way of watching.', 48, 0), (479958, 'It''s hard to see yourself as a princess because it involves a huge leap of the imagination and sort of requires you to believe you can be that, which is a scary, weird thing.', 67051, 0), (479959, 'I''m a light sleeper. I''ve never been one of those people who can put their head down and suddenly everything disappears. Nighttime is the time I get most scared, anxious or worried. In those darker moments before waking or sleeping is when I feel most, I don''t know, I can turn on myself, and my imagination can take me dark places.', 22790, 0), (479960, 'To have frequent recourse to narrative betrays great want of imagination.', 68382, 0), (479961, 'Novelists are not equipped to make a movie, in my opinion. They make their own movie when they write: they''re casting, they''re dressing the scene, they''re working out where the energy of the scene is coming from and they''re also relying tremendously on the creative imagination of the reader.', 5956, 0), (479962, 'Like every novelist, I fantasise about film. Novelists are not equipped to make a movie, in my opinion. They make their own movie when they write: they''re casting, they''re dressing the scene, they''re working out where the energy of the scene is coming from, and they''re also relying tremendously on the creative imagination of the reader.', 5956, 0), (479963, 'Being an actor in movies is a lot about the power of your imagination and making the circumstance real to you so the audience will feel that it''s real.', 68236, 0), (479964, 'Wit is the appearance, the external flash of imagination. Thus its divinity, and the witty character of mysticism.', 68443, 0), (479965, 'I seriously believed that my last hour was approaching, and yet, so strange is imagination, all I thought of was some childish hypothesis or other. In such circumstances, you do not choose your own thoughts. They overcome you.', 3205, 0), (479966, 'I think more influential than Emily Dickinson or Coleridge or Wordsworth on my imagination were Warner Brothers, Merrie Melodies, and Loony Tunes cartoons.', 8651, 0), (479967, 'Poetry can do a lot of things to people. I mean it can improve your imagination. It can take you to new places. It can give you this incredible form of verbal pleasure.', 8651, 0), (479968, 'I''m trying to write poems that involve beginning at a known place, and ending up at a slightly different place. I''m trying to take a little journey from one place to another, and it''s usually from a realistic place, to a place in the imagination.', 8651, 0), (479969, 'It''s not just that reporting gives you a bigger slice of life, gives - lends verisimilitude to what you are doing - it''s that it feeds the imagination.', 2476, 0), (479970, 'Our democracy, our constitutional framework is really a kind of software for harnessing the creativity and political imagination for all of our people. The American democratic system was an early political version of Napster.', 13473, 0), (479971, 'Essentially, I''m untrained, so I just go with my imagination and try to put myself as solidly as I can into the shoes of whatever person I''m going to be playing.', 67054, 0), (479972, 'Kashmir, the 86,000-square-mile region in India''s north, both is and isn''t the India of the popular imagination.', 767, 0), (479973, 'Memories, imagination, old sentiments, and associations are more readily reached through the sense of smell than through any other channel.', 24754, 0), (479974, 'Use your imagination, and you''ll see that even the most narrow, humdrum lives are infinite in scope if you examine them with enough care.', 1066, 0), (479975, 'I''m nosey, and I have a great imagination. So it''s not necessarily things I have to go through, but it''s things people I know or my family is going through, and I hear about it, and I think, ''That sounds like a great song.''', 70213, 0), (479976, 'The historical background is one of the easier aspects of writing a novel. Far more difficult is dreaming up the smaller, character-based scenes, scenes that rise entirely from one''s own imagination.', 31136, 0), (479977, 'I don''t think there is such a thing as pure imagination. I think it''s a combination of memory and invention.', 31136, 0), (479978, 'All my life I''ve had the privilege to make my living with my imagination, and the most important thing has been to see my creative life grow. I was educated to do that and have lived accordingly.', 10856, 0), (479979, 'Mr. Bergman had a great imagination and saw the possibilities within every one of his actors, and he gave us great challenges. It was very inspiring.', 68446, 0), (479980, 'There are casting directors with lots of imagination, but also some with not as much imagination.', 68446, 0), (479981, 'We humans lack imagination, to the point of not even knowing what tomorrow''s important things will look like.', 2505, 0), (479982, 'I had a good imagination and I still have one a child-like imagination that hasn''t gone away.', 10905, 0), (479983, 'The most important innovators often don''t need any technologies - just imagination and acute sensitivity to people''s needs.', 70907, 0), (479984, 'India lends itself well to fictionalization, but ultimately, it all depends on the writer''s imagination.', 2041, 0), (479985, 'Ghost stories really scare me. I have such a big imagination that after I watch a horror movie like ''The Grudge'', I look in the corners of my room for the next two days.', 67817, 0), (479986, 'Regrettably, with ''2001'' having a title that had a year in it, science fiction essentially set itself up in the public''s imagination as saying, ''Here''s what you get if you wait to that year.'' Well, we all waited till that year, and we didn''t get anything at all like that.', 13423, 0), (479987, 'You think in a different way when you don''t have any money. The joy of poverty is that you use your imagination to come up with stuff.', 274, 0), (479988, 'It''s a slight stretch of the imagination but most people are alike in most ways so I''ve never had any trouble identifying with the character that I''m playing.', 26129, 0), (479989, 'John Kerry had a very vivid imagination as a young person. I mean, he actually did go and take his bicycle from Norway to go camp in Sherwood Forest to be around the ghost of Robin Hood.', 19715, 0), (479990, 'If there is a book that the script came from you have to read it, you have to see what you can get out of it: mood, back story and things that may not even be in the film. They kick off your imagination and broaden the character, I think.', 68452, 0), (479991, 'My parents thought it was nice to develop my imagination, but they never seriously thought that anything would ever come of it. They said that I couldn''t be an actress because I would be taller than all my leading men, so I thought I would be a writer instead.', 754, 0), (479992, 'When one paints an ideal, one does not need to limit one''s imagination.', 62381, 0), (479993, 'There''s no great mystery to acting. It''s a very simple thing to do but you have to work hard at it. It''s about asking questions and using your imagination.', 74129, 0), (479994, 'I don''t think most books can be justifiably translated on screen. The film versions can''t convey the right emotion, fuel your imagination or allow you to visualise every line the way books do.', 66931, 0), (479995, 'My mom would always read a book to me at night from when I was three. Now, I can''t go to sleep without reading a book. At the same time, once I read, it''s difficult for me to go to sleep, as I have an overactive imagination and I start thinking.', 66931, 0), (479996, 'I see all these people talking about acting as a great spiritual thing. It''s not. There''s no great mystery to acting. It''s a very simple thing to do, but you have to work hard at it. It''s about asking questions and using your imagination.', 74129, 0), (479997, 'I have a very strong imagination and have since I was a little kid. That is where a lot of my world comes from. It''s like I''m off somewhere else. And I can have a problem in life because of that, because I''m always off in some other world thinking about something else. It''s constant.', 68454, 0), (479998, 'I''m not writing non-fiction. I don''t feel anything about me as a kid was unique. Except that I had more interest in being alone and using my imagination.', 850, 0), (479999, 'I don''t think it''s possible to touch people''s imagination today by aesthetic means.', 2312, 0), (480000, 'There''s a logic today that places a greater value on celebrity the less it is accompanied by actual achievement. I don''t think it''s possible to touch people''s imagination today by aesthetic means.', 2312, 0);
